WEBVTT

00:00.700 --> 00:02.901
<i> Previously on</i>
<i> "The Little Drummer Girl"...</i>

00:02.903 --> 00:05.337
When you showed me that boy
Michel, did you know

00:05.339 --> 00:06.772
you were going
to murder him?

00:08.275 --> 00:10.342
-Yes.
-Why didn't you tell me?

00:10.344 --> 00:12.144
We needed a genuine
performance.

00:12.146 --> 00:13.812
It will verify
your story now.

00:13.814 --> 00:16.482
Report upwards.
You're in this fight

00:16.484 --> 00:18.050
whether you
like it or not.

00:18.652 --> 00:20.386
-Boom!
-She has crossed a line

00:20.388 --> 00:22.421
God straighted.
-No, no, no, no, no, please!

00:22.423 --> 00:24.757
No!
-So now the fiction and reality

00:24.759 --> 00:25.724
become one.

00:25.726 --> 00:27.693
Welcome, Charlie.

00:27.695 --> 00:29.495
I am Fatmeh.

00:31.197 --> 00:39.304
♪♪

00:39.407 --> 00:43.208
Fatmeh: Salim was captured once
by the Jordanians.

00:43.310 --> 00:46.678
-And he was proud of it.
-Why?

00:46.781 --> 00:48.781
Because he was taken in
with Khalil.

00:48.883 --> 00:52.251
It was in the evening,
he said.

00:52.353 --> 00:54.653
A convoy of jeeps
came into the camp

00:54.755 --> 00:58.490
and they grabbed Khalil first,
then Salim.

00:58.592 --> 01:00.993
Then
they beat Khalil down.

01:01.095 --> 01:03.395
Took off his shoes
and made Salim hold his feet

01:03.497 --> 01:06.565
whilst they whipped them.

01:06.667 --> 01:08.934
And?

01:09.036 --> 01:10.869
Salim:
And then they change over.

01:10.971 --> 01:13.072
♪♪

01:13.174 --> 01:16.108
They whip me now.

01:16.210 --> 01:19.011
My brother is holding me.

01:19.113 --> 01:22.147
Our feet
aren't feet any more.

01:22.249 --> 01:23.916
They're unrecognizable.

01:24.018 --> 01:26.485
♪♪

01:26.587 --> 01:30.589
He said you nursed them
back to health.

01:30.691 --> 01:32.958
You bathed their feet,
read to them.

01:33.060 --> 01:35.394
♪♪

01:35.496 --> 01:37.896
And then you made them
plan new attacks.

01:37.998 --> 01:41.533
♪♪

01:41.635 --> 01:43.302
[Knocks on window]

01:43.404 --> 01:45.671
[Speaks Arabic]

01:45.773 --> 01:47.473
[Brakes squeak]

01:47.575 --> 01:50.142
[Van doors open]

01:50.244 --> 01:55.514
♪♪

01:55.616 --> 01:58.117
[Electricity buzzes]

01:58.219 --> 02:06.558
♪♪

02:06.660 --> 02:14.500
♪♪

02:14.602 --> 02:22.474
♪♪

02:22.576 --> 02:30.015
♪♪

02:30.117 --> 02:31.750
[Van door closes]

02:31.852 --> 02:36.188
[Engine revs]

02:36.290 --> 02:37.856
Wait! Salma!

02:37.958 --> 02:39.391
♪♪

02:39.493 --> 02:41.960
Wait!

02:42.062 --> 02:43.996
[Groans]

02:44.098 --> 02:47.166
[Bedsprings creak]

02:47.268 --> 02:50.269
[Siren wailing in distance]

02:50.371 --> 02:53.372
[Birds chirping]

03:04.351 --> 03:06.485
[Groans]

03:20.701 --> 03:23.702
[Vehicle approaching]

03:32.279 --> 03:39.251
♪♪

03:39.353 --> 03:42.721
[Brakes squeak]

03:42.823 --> 03:45.224
♪♪

03:45.326 --> 03:54.433
♪♪

03:54.535 --> 04:03.075
♪♪

04:03.177 --> 04:11.750
♪♪

04:11.852 --> 04:20.392
♪♪

04:20.494 --> 04:29.101
♪♪

04:29.203 --> 04:37.776
♪♪

04:37.878 --> 04:45.984
♪♪

04:46.086 --> 04:49.321
Okay! Everybody, off the truck!
Off the truck!

04:49.423 --> 04:50.522
-Move, move!
-Leave your stuff!

04:50.624 --> 04:52.724
Off the truck!
Women, this side!

04:52.826 --> 04:54.259
Everybody, hurry up!

04:54.361 --> 04:56.895
Halloran: All white scum
from the West, follow me!

04:56.997 --> 04:58.363
We got no drugs.

04:58.465 --> 05:00.065
No outside names.

05:00.167 --> 05:02.100
No personal
conversations.

05:02.202 --> 05:05.837
And never, ever enter
restricted-access areas.

05:05.939 --> 05:07.072
I want two lines.

05:07.174 --> 05:08.607
Looking at me,
facing me.

05:08.709 --> 05:10.509
Eyes on me.
Everybody.

05:10.611 --> 05:13.245
You, at the back,
hurry up!

05:13.347 --> 05:15.414
That's Captain Tayeh
in the jeep.

05:15.516 --> 05:17.949
He sets the rules
of the camp.

05:18.052 --> 05:21.486
If you break the rules,
you will be executed.

05:21.588 --> 05:24.456
[Gunshots]

05:24.558 --> 05:33.131
♪♪

05:46.246 --> 05:49.681
Rachel: Why has Rossino
been in London?

05:49.783 --> 05:53.952
Legal offices, a polytechnic,
a synagogue, some houses.

05:54.054 --> 05:56.555
-Targets?
-They can't all be targets.

05:56.657 --> 05:58.557
There's something else
linking them.

05:58.659 --> 06:00.225
Guess what?

06:00.327 --> 06:02.394
The Valkyrie's back
in town, too.

06:02.496 --> 06:03.695
Our good friend
Helga --

06:03.797 --> 06:06.264
she met with Mesterbein
yesterday.

06:06.367 --> 06:09.601
But still no word
on Charlie.

06:09.703 --> 06:12.604
I'm sorry, everyone.
It looks like we will be staying

06:12.706 --> 06:16.208
in this dank little country
a while longer.

06:16.310 --> 06:20.612
My comrades, who are we?

06:20.714 --> 06:21.880
We're the ones with no name.

06:21.982 --> 06:23.749
-Fire!
[Gunshots]

06:23.851 --> 06:26.651
No uniform.

06:26.754 --> 06:30.322
We are the grieving,
outraged mother,

06:30.424 --> 06:33.091
and we have come here to take up
our dead father's fight.

06:33.193 --> 06:35.060
Cease fire!

06:35.162 --> 06:40.399
♪♪

06:40.501 --> 06:41.800
Comrade Leila.

06:41.902 --> 06:43.435
Take aim!

06:43.537 --> 06:47.205
♪♪

06:47.307 --> 06:49.541
Who taught you to shoot
that way?

06:49.643 --> 06:51.243
Two on the right!

06:51.345 --> 06:52.744
Hands on your left!

06:52.846 --> 06:56.481
I shoot
with two hands!

06:56.583 --> 06:58.350
Two hands.
-Louder!

06:58.452 --> 06:59.918
[Groans]

07:00.020 --> 07:01.520
Two hands!

07:01.622 --> 07:03.221
Two hands!

07:03.323 --> 07:07.893
Halloran: We are the awakened
militant who has wasted too long

07:07.995 --> 07:12.731
on half-measures
and now stands, sword in hand.

07:12.833 --> 07:14.332
Fire!

07:14.435 --> 07:16.668
[Gunshot, explosion]
-We are you.

07:16.770 --> 07:18.437
We are me.

07:18.539 --> 07:21.807
We are the people.

07:21.909 --> 07:25.677
You are here to become a weapon
of the Palestinian cause.

07:25.779 --> 07:27.479
Comrade!

07:27.581 --> 07:30.248
Fire!
[Rocket fires, explosion]

07:30.350 --> 07:33.885
You will not indulge
in carnal pleasures.

07:33.987 --> 07:36.154
You will not ask questions
about operations

07:36.256 --> 07:38.190
that do not concern you.

07:38.292 --> 07:41.226
Captain Tayeh is training you
to be nothing.

07:41.328 --> 07:42.994
To need nothing.

07:43.096 --> 07:46.598
You are the armor-piercing shell
that will break

07:46.700 --> 07:48.834
the Western oppressor's heart.

07:48.936 --> 07:52.337
Trainer: This method gives one
hour from the time we set it.

07:52.439 --> 07:56.341
You must wind the hand back
at the last possible moment.

07:56.443 --> 07:58.143
There are some fools
who get so excited

07:58.245 --> 08:02.013
when the light bulb comes on
that they forget.

08:02.115 --> 08:03.181
Ding.

08:03.283 --> 08:04.950
Thuck.

08:05.052 --> 08:06.284
Boom.

08:06.386 --> 08:14.392
♪♪

08:14.495 --> 08:17.362
[Camera shutter clicking]

08:17.464 --> 08:20.532
♪♪

08:20.634 --> 08:22.133
[Car door closes]

08:22.236 --> 08:26.671
♪♪

08:26.773 --> 08:28.807
Rachel:
<i>Mesterbein's made the drop.</i>

08:28.909 --> 08:36.147
♪♪

08:36.250 --> 08:43.288
♪♪

08:43.390 --> 08:50.161
♪♪

08:50.264 --> 08:53.331
[Camera shutter clicks]

08:53.433 --> 08:55.300
♪♪

08:55.402 --> 08:56.768
[Camera shutter clicks]

08:56.870 --> 08:59.070
[Machine-gun fire]

08:59.172 --> 09:03.441
♪♪

09:03.544 --> 09:06.444
I said fire!

09:06.547 --> 09:08.613
♪♪

09:08.715 --> 09:12.250
[Screams]

09:12.352 --> 09:15.620
[Indistinct shouting]

09:15.722 --> 09:17.088
No, no, no!

09:17.190 --> 09:18.623
No, no, no!
I don't have to shoot.

09:18.725 --> 09:19.991
I don't have to fire.
I don't even have to --

09:20.093 --> 09:25.330
♪♪

09:25.432 --> 09:26.565
[Grunts]

09:26.667 --> 09:27.766
[Crowd gasps]

09:27.868 --> 09:30.669
[Laughs]

09:30.771 --> 09:33.705
[Grunts]

09:33.807 --> 09:35.574
♪♪

09:35.676 --> 09:37.442
Is everybody watching?

09:37.544 --> 09:39.311
Crowd: Yes.

09:39.413 --> 09:40.645
[Grunts]

09:40.747 --> 09:42.213
[Screams]

09:42.316 --> 09:45.951
[Cheers and applause]

09:46.053 --> 09:48.286
[Groans]

09:48.388 --> 09:52.424
[Panting]

09:52.526 --> 09:54.793
[Laughs]

09:54.895 --> 09:56.995
[Slides rattle]

09:57.097 --> 10:01.900
Rachel: So, Mesterbein posts
this, then returns to Zurich.

10:02.002 --> 10:04.869
It's an essay.
But it's nonsensical.

10:04.972 --> 10:07.005
Meaninglessness
filled with meaning.

10:07.107 --> 10:09.674
But who is it
intended for?

10:09.776 --> 10:13.111
The French observed
the pickup in Lyon.

10:13.213 --> 10:14.613
A factory worker.

10:14.715 --> 10:16.414
She hasn't moved since.

10:16.516 --> 10:19.384
She's not on their lists,
or ours.

10:19.486 --> 10:21.620
And what about
our other two beauties?

10:21.722 --> 10:23.655
Rossino's
still in the UK,

10:23.757 --> 10:26.024
and it looks like Helga's
shacked up with him.

10:26.126 --> 10:30.862
Isn't this handwriting
familiar to you, Mr. Schwilli?

10:30.964 --> 10:33.198
Michel's apartment.

10:40.774 --> 10:43.975
One to Germany,
one to France.

10:44.077 --> 10:45.977
Who is
communicating here?

10:46.079 --> 10:47.178
Daniel:
Mesterbein, of course.

10:47.280 --> 10:48.747
He wrote it.

10:48.849 --> 10:50.782
Who created it?

10:52.719 --> 10:54.953
If these are orders --

10:55.055 --> 10:56.888
Then why isn't
Rossino in France?

10:56.990 --> 10:58.356
Hmm.

10:58.458 --> 11:01.326
[Coughing in distance]

11:01.428 --> 11:07.899
♪♪

11:08.001 --> 11:13.338
♪♪

11:13.440 --> 11:15.240
Forget it.
Piss off.

11:15.342 --> 11:17.842
♪♪

11:17.944 --> 11:21.546
Halloran:
It gets lonely around here.

11:21.648 --> 11:23.948
I'm not lonely.

11:24.051 --> 11:25.750
Well,
you're gonna get lonely.

11:25.852 --> 11:29.187
♪♪

11:29.289 --> 11:31.723
Hey.

11:31.825 --> 11:33.358
What's your real name,
Leila?

11:33.460 --> 11:35.193
Read the rules,
Comrade Abdul.

11:35.295 --> 11:38.863
[Laughs] Shhh!

11:38.965 --> 11:40.432
Hey, listen.

11:40.534 --> 11:44.903
I -- I, um --
I-I just need something, okay?

11:45.005 --> 11:46.671
I just need something.

11:46.773 --> 11:48.773
They, uh, well, they don't --

11:48.875 --> 11:50.875
They don't know
what to do with me.

11:50.977 --> 11:52.343
[Laughs]

11:52.446 --> 11:57.148
I'm useless here,
and, uh, well,

11:57.250 --> 12:01.619
I'm a risk outside,
and, um, you see,

12:01.722 --> 12:04.089
I've been here --
I've been here

12:04.191 --> 12:07.192
I've been here two years,
two years,

12:07.294 --> 12:13.531
and, um, I've heard things
and -- and seen things.

12:13.633 --> 12:17.102
♪♪

12:17.204 --> 12:19.704
They're gonna kill me
any day now.

12:19.806 --> 12:24.743
I mean, I-I don't --
I don't ever eat too much food.

12:24.845 --> 12:28.146
I don't -- I don't even
use the soap

12:28.248 --> 12:30.148
in case
I cost them too much.

12:30.250 --> 12:33.418
Hey, hey.
Shhhh.

12:33.520 --> 12:36.721
You're doing really well here
and -- and --

12:36.823 --> 12:38.423
and you'll be leaving soon.

12:38.525 --> 12:43.294
And look, I worked out the map
coordinates to this place, yeah?

12:43.396 --> 12:50.502
And they're, uh, uh,
333 --

12:50.604 --> 12:55.974
33/44/38.4 north.

12:56.076 --> 13:01.346
33/25/17 east.

13:01.448 --> 13:02.680
And, um, look, look,
look, look, look.

13:02.783 --> 13:04.249
All --
All you've gotta do, um --

13:04.351 --> 13:06.351
you just, uh -- you just --

13:06.453 --> 13:08.987
you just drop a note
to the US Embassy, okay?

13:09.089 --> 13:15.126
And you just -- you just say
that, um, that Arthur --

13:15.228 --> 13:19.631
Arthur A. Halloran,
yeah?

13:19.733 --> 13:24.669
He'd -- He'd like --
He'd like to come home and --

13:24.771 --> 13:28.306
and pay his debt
to society, okay?

13:28.408 --> 13:32.210
Okay.

13:32.312 --> 13:36.748
Yeah. My m-- My mom would
visit me in prison, I think.

13:36.850 --> 13:38.316
I think w-- she would.
Now listen, listen.

13:38.418 --> 13:41.252
Listen, her name -- her name --
her name is Janet.

13:41.354 --> 13:42.654
What's yours?
I mean, what's your name?

13:42.756 --> 13:44.689
-Okay. Okay.
-I mean, I told you my name.

13:44.791 --> 13:46.457
Come on, I told you my name.
-Okay.

13:46.560 --> 13:48.026
What's your --
Okay. Okay.

13:48.128 --> 13:50.495
Okay. Hey.

13:50.597 --> 13:51.830
Hey.

13:51.932 --> 13:53.164
Hey.

13:53.266 --> 13:54.365
It's okay.
I'm sorry.

13:54.467 --> 13:56.034
I went too far.
I went too far.

13:56.136 --> 13:59.237
It's been a really,
really great night and, uh, um,

13:59.339 --> 14:02.740
uh, a-and I'm --
I'm sorry, and --

14:02.843 --> 14:04.475
For all I know they sent
you here to test me.

14:04.578 --> 14:06.277
Get out. Get out!
Get out, get out.
No.

14:06.379 --> 14:07.478
Shhhh! Shhhh!

14:07.581 --> 14:09.714
Get out.

14:09.816 --> 14:11.516
[Breathing heavily]

14:11.618 --> 14:14.986
♪♪

14:33.539 --> 14:36.574
[Birds chirping]

14:51.892 --> 14:54.659
[Rooster crows]

15:07.173 --> 15:10.441
[Charlie breathing heavily]

15:33.433 --> 15:35.433
[Paper rustles]

15:46.947 --> 15:49.747
Halloran: You know what
the penalty for spying is?

15:49.883 --> 15:50.949
Huh? [Laughs]

15:51.084 --> 15:54.585
Oh, now,
Tayeh's gonna love me!

15:54.721 --> 15:56.521
♪♪

15:56.656 --> 15:59.223
Hey! Hey! Hey! Hey!
We got a spy! We got a spy!

15:59.326 --> 16:01.893
-Hold it!
-We got a traitor!

16:01.995 --> 16:04.495
Halloran: You see, I caught her
spying, ladies and gentlemen.

16:04.631 --> 16:07.098
She's a traitor.

16:07.233 --> 16:08.433
I told you I was useful,
man.

16:08.568 --> 16:09.767
He's lying.

16:09.869 --> 16:11.436
I only went in there
to report him.

16:11.571 --> 16:12.770
He tried to
jump me last night.

16:12.872 --> 16:16.641
Oh, the bullshit of Babylon,
right there!

16:16.776 --> 16:18.943
She came on to me.

16:19.045 --> 16:20.311
Okay?
-Ha!

16:20.413 --> 16:22.847
So I told her the rules.

16:22.983 --> 16:25.016
Does anyone
believe that?

16:25.151 --> 16:28.786
As if I would seduce
Comrade Abdul?

16:28.922 --> 16:34.158
[Laughter]

16:35.628 --> 16:37.862
[Speaks Arabic]

16:37.931 --> 16:41.032
♪♪

16:41.167 --> 16:42.433
-Hey. Wait.
-Yes.

16:42.535 --> 16:45.169
Wait, wait, wait! Wait!
Hey! Hey!

16:45.271 --> 16:49.240
Why would you step in there
without permission?

16:49.342 --> 16:51.843
You know the penalty
for spying is execution.

16:51.978 --> 16:54.178
Yes, yes, yes!

16:54.314 --> 16:56.014
Comrade Abdul
broke the law.

16:56.149 --> 16:58.716
No private conversations.

16:58.818 --> 16:59.984
You are a liar.

17:00.120 --> 17:01.352
[Panting]

17:01.488 --> 17:02.987
[Laughing]

17:03.123 --> 17:04.255
Arthur A. Halloran!

17:04.357 --> 17:05.523
[Stops laughing]

17:05.658 --> 17:08.259
♪♪

17:08.361 --> 17:12.497
That's his real name,
right?

17:12.632 --> 17:16.100
He told me that
last night.

17:16.236 --> 17:18.636
He asked that I go
into an embassy

17:18.705 --> 17:21.639
and say that
he could betray us

17:21.775 --> 17:25.743
and that his mother
would visit him in prison.

17:25.845 --> 17:28.212
And her name's Janet.

17:28.348 --> 17:30.848
♪♪

17:30.984 --> 17:33.017
How would I know that
if I were lying?

17:33.153 --> 17:34.719
♪♪

17:34.821 --> 17:37.321
[Crowd murmuring]

17:37.424 --> 17:41.926
♪♪

17:42.062 --> 17:43.961
[Speaks Arabic]

17:44.064 --> 17:49.467
♪♪

17:49.536 --> 17:51.235
Whoa! Whoa!
Whoa!

17:51.337 --> 17:54.639
What? What? What?

17:54.741 --> 17:57.842
Come on, man!
Come on!

17:57.977 --> 17:59.877
I just -- I just --

18:00.013 --> 18:02.080
I just told her that
to get her to put out.

18:02.215 --> 18:04.015
Tayeh, that's --
that's all, man.

18:04.117 --> 18:06.317
Come on.

18:06.419 --> 18:09.320
Come on.

18:09.422 --> 18:10.555
Please.

18:10.690 --> 18:13.458
Please.

18:13.560 --> 18:14.792
[Gasps]

18:14.928 --> 18:16.260
Hey!

18:16.362 --> 18:19.230
[Indistinct shouting]

18:19.332 --> 18:22.100
♪♪

18:22.235 --> 18:24.102
[Gunshots]

18:24.204 --> 18:29.774
♪♪

18:29.876 --> 18:31.642
[Gun clicks empty]

18:31.778 --> 18:33.144
[Shouts in Arabic]

18:33.246 --> 18:34.912
[Machine-gun fire]

18:35.048 --> 18:43.821
♪♪

18:43.957 --> 18:45.156
[Paper rustles]

18:45.291 --> 18:47.492
Pack your bag, comrade.

18:51.131 --> 18:54.599
[Breathes shakily]

18:54.734 --> 18:57.735
[Crowd murmuring]

19:09.649 --> 19:11.282
We've got something.

19:11.417 --> 19:12.683
[Claps hands]

19:12.785 --> 19:14.552
[Silverware clinks]

19:14.654 --> 19:18.022
[Papers rustle]

19:18.158 --> 19:21.392
We counted the number
of characters in each sentence

19:21.494 --> 19:23.761
and applied that
to the ASCII key code.

19:23.897 --> 19:25.163
Daniel:
You get whole words.

19:25.298 --> 19:26.797
<i>"Défense"</i> for the French
postcard,

19:26.933 --> 19:28.866
<i> "Vergiss"</i>
for the German one.

19:28.968 --> 19:32.670
Which translate to "defense"
and "forget."

19:32.739 --> 19:34.639
Progress.

19:34.741 --> 19:36.407
But they're still
meaningless.

19:36.509 --> 19:39.010
[Telex machine clicking]

19:39.078 --> 19:42.313
What's he after here?

19:42.448 --> 19:44.882
This isn't about killing
for him.

19:45.018 --> 19:47.285
It's about the show.

19:47.420 --> 19:50.154
They're preparing Charlie
for something.

19:50.223 --> 19:51.923
For what?

19:52.025 --> 19:53.958
Marty?

20:03.970 --> 20:05.269
[Radio clicks on]

20:05.371 --> 20:07.271
Reporter:
<i>Bodies are still being counted,</i>

20:07.373 --> 20:09.106
<i> but an Israeli journalist</i>

20:09.242 --> 20:11.943
<i> attending the conference</i>
<i> in Lyon today with his family</i>

20:12.078 --> 20:13.544
<i> is believed</i>
<i> to have been the main tar--</i>

20:13.680 --> 20:15.713
[Radio turns off]

20:19.052 --> 20:21.652
[Sighs]

20:21.754 --> 20:25.623
Ask the French
if there was a wire doll.

20:25.758 --> 20:28.559
We're fools!

20:28.661 --> 20:30.928
Khalil has another cell.

20:31.030 --> 20:33.831
Now, if you want a return
on your investment --

20:33.967 --> 20:36.534
Gavron:<i> So I'm the schmuck,</i>
<i> the money-man.</i>

20:36.603 --> 20:38.302
<i> Martin Kurtz</i>
<i> is the talent!</i>

20:38.404 --> 20:40.905
We're getting closer!

20:41.007 --> 20:43.541
Do you really think
bombing a few camps

20:43.676 --> 20:44.942
is going to
stop him now?

20:45.044 --> 20:47.478
They are bombing us,
Marty!

20:51.985 --> 20:54.885
Charlie is in Lebanon.

20:55.021 --> 20:56.887
She is on the inside.

20:57.023 --> 20:58.656
Where?

20:58.791 --> 21:00.858
<i> Well, then.</i>

21:00.994 --> 21:03.561
<i> Wouldn't he expect</i>
<i>a response to this attack?</i>

21:03.663 --> 21:07.331
<i>And if it doesn't come,</i>
<i>won't that make him suspicious?</i>

21:07.400 --> 21:09.700
<i> I answer to the people, Marty.</i>
<i> Not you.</i>

21:09.802 --> 21:11.669
-Noah? It's Gadi. D--
<i> [Receiver clicks]</i>

21:16.843 --> 21:20.278
[Receiver thuds]

21:21.913 --> 21:23.147
[Horn honking]

21:23.249 --> 21:24.382
[Children shouting, laughing]

21:24.484 --> 21:25.850
[Bicycle bell dings]

21:25.985 --> 21:29.720
[Speaking Arabic]

21:29.822 --> 21:31.055
[Brakes squeak]

21:31.157 --> 21:33.491
[Horn honks]

21:33.593 --> 21:40.665
♪♪

21:40.767 --> 21:42.700
Ah,<i> oui.</i>

21:42.769 --> 21:45.436
Thank you.

21:45.505 --> 21:47.605
Kareem: Salma!

21:47.707 --> 21:52.910
♪♪

21:53.046 --> 21:56.280
[Gun clicks]

21:56.416 --> 21:59.984
[Gun cocks]

22:00.053 --> 22:02.253
[Bullet clinks]

22:02.388 --> 22:06.157
[Gunshots]

22:06.292 --> 22:08.359
<i> Shukran.</i>

22:08.461 --> 22:10.227
I'm Kareem.

22:10.363 --> 22:11.429
Leila.

22:11.531 --> 22:13.130
You can
be Charlie here.

22:13.266 --> 22:16.167
♪♪

22:16.302 --> 22:19.236
It is a rule of the camp
that buildings

22:19.339 --> 22:20.871
should not be permanent,

22:21.007 --> 22:23.474
in case we forget
where our true home is.

22:23.609 --> 22:28.646
♪♪

22:28.748 --> 22:32.149
[Curtain rattles]

22:37.256 --> 22:39.557
[Speaks Arabic]

22:45.498 --> 22:47.765
[Pills rattle]

22:47.900 --> 22:50.901
[Speaking Arabic]

22:55.708 --> 22:57.041
<i> Shukran,</i> Fatmeh.

22:57.143 --> 23:00.678
[Speaks Arabic]

23:06.586 --> 23:08.152
You're a doctor?

23:08.254 --> 23:09.487
Yeah.

23:09.622 --> 23:11.455
We have to be a little
of everything here.

23:11.557 --> 23:13.157
Sit.

23:31.177 --> 23:35.413
We shall celebrate
our fallen brothers.

23:35.515 --> 23:39.383
Becker: They'll make you feel
like you belong, Charlie.

23:39.485 --> 23:41.552
You'll become ashamed
of deceiving them.

23:41.654 --> 23:43.621
♪♪

23:43.756 --> 23:46.490
You might even decide
to tell them the truth.

23:46.592 --> 23:52.396
But the second you do,
they will turn on you.

23:52.532 --> 23:54.765
Torture you.

23:54.901 --> 23:57.735
Kill you.

23:57.804 --> 23:59.537
I read
your letters to him.

23:59.672 --> 24:02.673
[Envelope rustles]

24:07.947 --> 24:09.713
Your diary.

24:12.452 --> 24:15.519
[Diary thuds]

24:15.655 --> 24:18.756
You do not love Salim.

24:18.858 --> 24:20.758
You love his death.

24:25.565 --> 24:27.498
They are
the same thing now.

24:29.435 --> 24:32.403
Yeah.

24:32.538 --> 24:35.539
Maybe.

24:35.675 --> 24:38.142
People in our world,
Charlie,

24:38.244 --> 24:41.445
they will be
drawn to you...

24:41.547 --> 24:45.115
because you can lie.

24:45.251 --> 24:48.853
Because you have a pretty
white face and a clean passport.

24:52.425 --> 24:55.759
I brought you here
because I want you to be true.

25:00.566 --> 25:06.871
How was he,
the last time you saw him?

25:06.973 --> 25:09.039
Please?

25:09.141 --> 25:11.408
♪♪

25:11.544 --> 25:13.444
Honestly?

25:13.546 --> 25:15.346
Yeah.

25:15.481 --> 25:21.085
♪♪

25:21.220 --> 25:24.188
He was vulnerable,

25:24.290 --> 25:26.557
and he could barely move.

25:26.659 --> 25:28.425
Why?

25:28.528 --> 25:34.064
♪♪

25:34.200 --> 25:36.567
Oh. [Clears throat]
I see.

25:36.669 --> 25:40.371
You and he
had a fantastic night.

25:40.473 --> 25:43.374
I understand.

25:43.476 --> 25:45.609
I understand.

25:45.745 --> 25:54.084
♪♪

25:54.220 --> 25:56.387
[Sniffs]

25:56.489 --> 26:04.428
♪♪

26:04.564 --> 26:06.664
We found a new postcard,
Gadi.

26:08.534 --> 26:11.335
We got it
from Rossino's flat.

26:11.437 --> 26:14.371
He collected it from a PO Box
yesterday.

26:14.507 --> 26:18.075
And now England.

26:18.144 --> 26:21.111
[Both speaking Arabic]

26:25.251 --> 26:26.417
[Laughs]

26:26.485 --> 26:28.485
What? Stop!

26:28.621 --> 26:29.720
I'm trying.

26:29.855 --> 26:31.221
Okay.

26:34.527 --> 26:36.560
[Speaks Arabic]

26:41.567 --> 26:42.633
[Laughter]

26:42.768 --> 26:44.168
[Speaks Arabic]

26:44.303 --> 26:46.103
-[Speaks Arabic]
-[Speaks Arabic]

26:46.205 --> 26:48.606
Oh, you find me funny, too,
do you?

26:48.741 --> 26:50.407
I'm trying.

26:50.543 --> 26:51.809
No. No.

26:51.944 --> 26:54.478
You are<i> 'armalat alshahid.</i>

26:54.580 --> 26:56.347
We respect that.

26:56.482 --> 26:57.715
What's --
What's that?

26:57.850 --> 27:00.117
Um, a-a martyr's widow.

27:00.252 --> 27:02.419
-Oh.
-We are, too, in a way.

27:02.521 --> 27:05.656
Yasir and I.

27:05.791 --> 27:07.091
And we're glad
you have come.

27:07.226 --> 27:09.059
How -- How do you say, um,

27:09.195 --> 27:11.095
"good -- good luck,
best wishes"?

27:11.230 --> 27:12.296
<i> Bin na jeh.</i>

27:12.398 --> 27:13.631
[Speaks Arabic]

27:13.766 --> 27:15.733
[Laughter]

27:15.835 --> 27:17.768
What?
You told me to say that!

27:17.870 --> 27:18.969
What did I just say?

27:19.105 --> 27:20.938
<i> Bin na jeh.</i>

27:21.007 --> 27:22.706
-Huh?
<i> -Na jeh.</i>

27:22.808 --> 27:25.609
That's what I said,
<i> na jah.</i>

27:25.745 --> 27:27.945
<i> -Na jeh.</i>
<i> -Na jeh.</i>

27:28.080 --> 27:30.047
[Laughter]

27:41.594 --> 27:44.595
[Paper rustles]

27:50.269 --> 27:52.269
Well.

27:52.405 --> 27:54.638
We all know what that means.

27:57.342 --> 28:01.311
[Speaking Arabic]

28:01.414 --> 28:03.814
[Gunshot]

28:03.916 --> 28:06.717
[Crowd singing in Arabic,
gunfire]

28:06.852 --> 28:13.557
♪♪

28:13.659 --> 28:19.430
♪♪

28:19.565 --> 28:23.100
[Horn honks]

28:23.202 --> 28:31.909
♪♪

28:32.044 --> 28:40.250
♪♪

28:40.386 --> 28:48.158
♪♪

28:48.260 --> 28:51.028
Charlie!

28:51.163 --> 29:00.537
♪♪

29:00.673 --> 29:02.706
[Gun cocks]

29:02.808 --> 29:05.476
[Gunshots]

29:05.578 --> 29:07.878
[Music stops]

29:09.882 --> 29:11.081
Crowd: Salim!

29:11.217 --> 29:13.050
-Salim!
-Salim!

29:13.185 --> 29:14.918
-Salim!
-Salim!

29:15.054 --> 29:16.787
-Salim!
-Salim!

29:16.889 --> 29:18.489
-Salim!
-Salim!

29:18.624 --> 29:19.990
-Salim!
-Salim!

29:20.092 --> 29:22.059
-Salim!
-Salim!

29:22.194 --> 29:24.294
-Khalil!
-Khalil!

29:24.396 --> 29:26.230
-Khalil!
-Khalil!

29:26.365 --> 29:27.931
-Khalil!
-Khalil!

29:28.033 --> 29:30.901
[All chanting "Khalil!"]

29:31.003 --> 29:36.573
♪♪

29:36.709 --> 29:38.008
Maram!

29:38.144 --> 29:40.711
[Chanting continues]

29:40.846 --> 29:43.280
[Shouting indistinctly]

29:43.382 --> 29:45.115
Maram, come down!

29:45.251 --> 29:46.717
[Chanting continues]

29:46.852 --> 29:48.552
I can't --

29:48.687 --> 29:51.522
[Shouts indistinctly]

29:51.657 --> 29:52.990
♪♪

29:53.092 --> 29:55.125
[Jets approaching]

29:55.261 --> 29:56.293
[Explosion]

29:56.428 --> 29:58.695
[Screaming]

29:58.831 --> 30:05.202
♪♪

30:05.337 --> 30:06.937
[Explosion]

30:07.039 --> 30:13.644
♪♪

30:13.746 --> 30:19.449
♪♪

30:19.518 --> 30:21.952
[Flames crackling]

30:22.087 --> 30:28.826
♪♪

30:28.928 --> 30:30.894
Michel:<i> Al Nakba.</i>

30:31.030 --> 30:32.996
<i> Al Nakba!</i>
<i> Al Nakba!</i>

30:33.098 --> 30:37.067
<i> Al Nakba!</i>
<i> Al Nakba!</i>

30:37.203 --> 30:44.241
♪♪

30:44.376 --> 30:50.314
♪♪

31:04.296 --> 31:06.296
Five camps.

31:09.435 --> 31:11.401
I am sorry.

31:17.776 --> 31:20.777
<i> [Man speaking indistinctly</i>
<i> on radio]</i>

31:27.553 --> 31:29.887
[Chalk scraping]

31:29.989 --> 31:35.659
♪♪

31:35.761 --> 31:39.663
The war of Independence,
1948.

31:39.798 --> 31:40.864
What do they call it?

31:41.000 --> 31:42.232
"The Catastrophe."

31:42.368 --> 31:44.034
-Or --
-"Disaster."

31:44.169 --> 31:47.504
♪♪

31:47.640 --> 31:51.074
-Who started all this?
-The British.

31:51.176 --> 31:53.844
Now, Khalil isn't
attacking people.

31:53.946 --> 31:56.413
He's attacking ideas.

31:56.515 --> 31:59.383
The theater of the real.

31:59.485 --> 32:01.084
He needs people's attention

32:01.186 --> 32:02.753
because without an audience,
there's nothing.

32:02.888 --> 32:04.488
Khalil is a showman.

32:04.590 --> 32:06.523
Helga, Rossino.

32:06.659 --> 32:08.225
They're in England.
-Yes.

32:08.327 --> 32:09.960
What about Charlie?

32:10.095 --> 32:12.429
A British girl
on British soil.

32:12.531 --> 32:14.498
He won't be able
to resist.

32:14.600 --> 32:17.467
The other postcards broke down
to two words,

32:17.603 --> 32:19.036
"Defense" and "Forget."

32:19.171 --> 32:20.871
And both victims
were ideologues.

32:21.006 --> 32:25.142
The journalist in Lyon, Rosen,
he was set to give a speech.

32:25.244 --> 32:27.344
"Défense Offensive."

32:27.446 --> 32:29.379
"Défense."

32:29.515 --> 32:30.614
Bad Godesberg.

32:30.749 --> 32:32.883
Fineberg's uncle,
the scholar --

32:32.985 --> 32:36.286
He was writing about Germany,
about the Holocaust.

32:36.388 --> 32:38.388
W-W-What was the name
of his new book?

32:38.524 --> 32:40.524
<i> -"Vergiss Nicht."</i>
-"Never forget."

32:40.659 --> 32:44.127
♪♪

32:44.263 --> 32:45.929
Miss Bach: So, to sum up.

32:46.065 --> 32:50.334
First, the date -- the word
"Disaster" gives us<i> Al Nakba.</i>

32:50.469 --> 32:52.669
Litvak: The anniversary's
on the 15th of May.

32:52.805 --> 32:55.806
Becker: Second, the location --

32:55.908 --> 32:59.343
the British are responsible
for<i> Al Nakba.</i>

32:59.445 --> 33:01.611
Britain.

33:01.747 --> 33:05.782
♪♪

33:05.918 --> 33:08.919
The Israelis
will strike back.

33:09.021 --> 33:11.388
Without a response,

33:11.523 --> 33:13.890
we are just
a few Arabs in the dust.

33:13.993 --> 33:16.393
♪♪

33:16.528 --> 33:19.062
Don't you understand?

33:19.164 --> 33:22.632
For the Palestinians
even to exist,

33:22.735 --> 33:26.003
we must lift
the world up by the neck.

33:26.071 --> 33:28.839
Kurtz: Third, the target --

33:28.907 --> 33:33.377
thinkers,
so they wound us more deeply.

33:33.479 --> 33:36.880
And when they strike back,
we will strike back again,

33:36.982 --> 33:39.282
and again, and again.

33:39.418 --> 33:41.952
♪♪

33:42.054 --> 33:43.787
Yes.

33:43.922 --> 33:47.357
The anniversary of<i> Al Nakba</i>
is in three days' time.

33:47.493 --> 33:50.060
We look for any event
on the 15th --

33:50.162 --> 33:52.229
anything that might
tie to disaster,

33:52.331 --> 33:54.698
catastrophe,
independence,<i> Al Nakba.</i>

33:54.833 --> 33:56.366
Anything even close!

33:56.502 --> 34:00.237
♪♪

34:00.305 --> 34:03.073
Gadi, I want you
to take another look

34:03.208 --> 34:05.008
at the sites Rossino visited.

34:05.110 --> 34:11.014
♪♪

34:11.150 --> 34:16.019
♪♪

34:16.155 --> 34:20.023
Becker: I am at the Polytechnic
of Greater London.

34:20.125 --> 34:21.958
An Israeli professor
is holding a talk here

34:22.094 --> 34:24.861
on the anniversary
of<i> Al Nakba.</i>

34:24.963 --> 34:28.665
The word "Disaster" is in
the title of her lecture.

34:34.505 --> 34:36.840
Why not have a flashing light
and a siren, too?

34:36.975 --> 34:39.843
Oh, play nicely,
Shimon.

34:39.978 --> 34:43.146
It's our ball,
but their court.

34:49.988 --> 34:52.122
He's been looking forward
to this, you know, sir.

34:52.257 --> 34:53.957
Immensely.

34:56.862 --> 35:00.063
[Indistinct conversations]

35:00.165 --> 35:01.731
This way, sir.

35:01.867 --> 35:05.235
[Telephone rings]

35:12.444 --> 35:15.378
[Papers rustle]

35:18.951 --> 35:21.718
Mr. Raphael,

35:21.820 --> 35:23.186
meet Captain Meadows.

35:23.288 --> 35:26.490
Captain Meadows,
meet Mr. Raphael.

35:26.592 --> 35:27.724
From Tel Aviv.

35:27.860 --> 35:29.893
An honor, sir, actually.

35:29.995 --> 35:33.330
[Clears throat]

35:45.811 --> 35:47.043
Fine moustache.

35:47.179 --> 35:49.146
Hmm.

35:51.483 --> 35:53.917
[Chairs scrape floor]

36:00.759 --> 36:03.160
I knew a Raphael once.

36:03.295 --> 36:07.164
Some shit-heap town
in the Golan Heights.

36:07.266 --> 36:10.167
You were probably
just a kid back then.

36:10.302 --> 36:12.802
Fighting with the Irgun,
no doubt,

36:12.905 --> 36:14.538
like your mucker Gavron.

36:14.673 --> 36:17.641
[Teacup clinks]

36:25.784 --> 36:28.218
Anton Mester-been.

36:28.353 --> 36:30.720
Mesterbein.

36:30.822 --> 36:33.390
He runs a legal practice
out of Zurich,

36:33.525 --> 36:35.625
from which
he offers representation

36:35.761 --> 36:38.728
to a variety of
rather radical organizations.

36:42.901 --> 36:44.100
Who's the woman?

36:44.236 --> 36:46.102
Frau Astrid Berger,

36:46.238 --> 36:48.104
alias Edda Schmidt.

36:48.240 --> 36:50.473
Currently going by
Helga Stern.

36:50.542 --> 36:54.177
No Mesterbein on the magic box,
sir, sorry, not even a POI.

36:54.279 --> 36:56.112
Well, we've moved on,  Meadows.

36:56.248 --> 37:00.951
Astrid Berger, Edda Schmidt,
Helga Stern.

37:01.053 --> 37:03.153
Your ignorance here
is no reflection

37:03.255 --> 37:05.989
on your excellent
records department, Commander.

37:06.124 --> 37:07.457
Until a short time ago,

37:07.559 --> 37:11.094
we were also unaware
of Mesterbein's dalliances.

37:11.196 --> 37:12.963
What enlightened you?

37:18.570 --> 37:20.103
Well,
that one I know.

37:20.239 --> 37:21.905
He's the genius who scored
an own-goal

37:22.040 --> 37:24.674
on the Munich autobahn,
yes?

37:24.810 --> 37:27.844
Same chap we pointed out to you
at that poxy forum.

37:27.946 --> 37:30.914
And we were very grateful,
too.

37:31.049 --> 37:33.883
Because since then,
our sources have revealed

37:34.019 --> 37:38.722
that all of these players
are part of the same cell.

37:38.824 --> 37:42.726
And now they're all holidaying
in England, hmm?

37:42.828 --> 37:44.828
Hmm.

37:44.930 --> 37:49.599
Do you know anything about
an English bird, Charmian Ross?

37:49.735 --> 37:52.335
She was
at that forum, too.

37:52.437 --> 37:55.171
Last seen crossing all sorts
of unfamiliar borders

37:55.274 --> 37:57.907
in a car not dissimilar
to that driven by

37:58.043 --> 38:00.577
your toasty
Arab friend there.

38:00.712 --> 38:03.647
Now we have Mossad agents
crawling all over London.

38:03.749 --> 38:07.784
Hell of a coincidence,
don't you think?

38:07.886 --> 38:10.353
-Hmm.
-Mm.

38:10.455 --> 38:14.491
Meadows: NRA on Berger, Stern,
or Schmidt, either, Sir.

38:14.626 --> 38:17.360
For God's sake,
Meadows.

38:17.462 --> 38:21.197
This picture was taken
by a lucky chance in Greece.

38:21.333 --> 38:23.400
Oh, she's definitely
on our system, sir.

38:23.535 --> 38:24.701
We know her
from the forum, too.

38:24.803 --> 38:27.771
I am proud of you,
Meadows.

38:27.906 --> 38:30.040
[Papers rustle]

38:31.943 --> 38:34.344
I think Mr. Raphael and I
could do

38:34.479 --> 38:37.147
with a breath
of English fresh air.

38:39.284 --> 38:42.819
Get all that from that kraut
ninny Dr. Alexis, did you?

38:42.921 --> 38:45.555
I am told he has been
a most accommodating ally.

38:45.657 --> 38:47.557
Oh, yeah?

38:47.659 --> 38:49.159
Funny.

38:49.261 --> 38:52.662
The only Israeli he said he'd
dealt with was a "Schulmann."

38:52.764 --> 38:56.166
Had a little whippet,
never caught the name.

38:56.301 --> 38:58.868
Do you know any Schulmanns,
Mr. Raphael?

39:01.707 --> 39:04.674
You see, it's one thing
to piss on my leg

39:04.776 --> 39:06.676
and tell me
that it's raining.

39:06.778 --> 39:09.112
It's quite another to take
a bloody great shit

39:09.247 --> 39:12.716
all over me without the courtesy
of a weather report.

39:12.818 --> 39:14.617
♪♪

39:14.720 --> 39:16.086
Come off it.

39:16.221 --> 39:19.222
Operation Mincemeat,
we invented that.

39:19.291 --> 39:21.458
Find a corpse,
stuff it with disinformation,

39:21.560 --> 39:24.327
leave it somewhere
for the enemy to find.

39:24.429 --> 39:26.396
I have a hunch, though,
that you clever lot

39:26.498 --> 39:28.565
have taken it
one step further.

39:28.667 --> 39:30.600
No dead meat to hand
so you find yourselves

39:30.702 --> 39:32.369
some nice fresh meat
and bumf!

39:32.504 --> 39:35.205
Blow it up
in a Mercedes.

39:35.340 --> 39:37.540
And now they've bitten.

39:37.676 --> 39:38.975
I bet you're chuffed
to the bullocks

39:39.077 --> 39:41.111
with yourselves,
aren't you?

39:41.213 --> 39:42.345
Yeah.

39:42.481 --> 39:44.681
On my desk, Williams,
please.

39:44.816 --> 39:49.319
[Door opens]

39:49.454 --> 39:53.256
♪♪

39:53.392 --> 39:56.826
[Door closes]

39:56.962 --> 40:02.031
♪♪

40:02.167 --> 40:04.267
I am ready.

40:04.369 --> 40:05.802
♪♪

40:05.937 --> 40:07.771
Whenever you say.

40:07.906 --> 40:15.812
♪♪

40:15.914 --> 40:23.453
♪♪

40:23.555 --> 40:30.493
♪♪

40:30.629 --> 40:32.462
Picton: We let them in?

40:34.966 --> 40:37.600
And let them explode the bomb.
Yes.

40:37.736 --> 40:39.936
In my bloody country?

40:40.038 --> 40:44.941
An attack you can control is
better than one you concede.

40:45.010 --> 40:46.810
Who says we conceded?

40:46.945 --> 40:48.778
The Irish.
The UVF.

40:48.914 --> 40:52.215
Anyone
who tries their luck.

40:52.350 --> 40:55.385
You will be given full credit
for any success we have.

40:55.520 --> 40:57.320
Public acclaim.

40:57.456 --> 40:59.422
Yeah, and all the crap
when it goes wrong.

40:59.524 --> 41:02.892
[Chickens clucking]

41:03.028 --> 41:04.694
Go on, on you go.
Chop, chop, chop.

41:04.796 --> 41:07.831
chop, chop,
chop, chop, chop!

41:11.570 --> 41:16.606
Do you know,
back in '47,

41:16.708 --> 41:20.577
when I was still
a junior,

41:20.712 --> 41:24.013
we took in this little Israeli
shit for questioning.

41:24.149 --> 41:26.416
The same town
in the Golan Heights.

41:27.752 --> 41:33.623
A gang of kids had been taking
pot shots at my men, you see.

41:33.725 --> 41:38.127
And I was sure that this boy
was a weak link,

41:38.263 --> 41:42.332
sure he'd spill the names.

41:42.434 --> 41:46.803
But the harder I pushed,
the quieter he got.

41:46.905 --> 41:48.972
Nearly broke
my bloody hand.

41:49.074 --> 41:51.174
But he didn't
breathe a word.

41:51.309 --> 41:53.543
Not one name.

41:53.612 --> 41:56.746
When I let him go,
I thought to myself,

41:56.882 --> 42:00.683
"God, if I haven't made
a little drummer boy right here,

42:00.785 --> 42:03.286
ready to bang his gong
into the next battle

42:03.388 --> 42:05.955
they find for him,
I don't know what I've done."

42:09.060 --> 42:12.896
Half the kids in that town
went on to become Irgun.

42:13.031 --> 42:16.366
Bloody Zionist thugs.

42:16.468 --> 42:18.935
Next year they marched
into the Palestinian village

42:19.070 --> 42:21.771
of Deir Yassin.

42:21.873 --> 42:24.374
Most vicious slaughter
I've ever seen.

42:41.993 --> 42:45.662
[Radio static]

42:45.764 --> 42:48.064
Gadi was right,
Marty.

42:48.199 --> 42:50.233
It's Professor Minkel.

42:50.335 --> 42:53.002
Rossino's locations
were all hers.

42:53.104 --> 42:55.371
Every one
is on her itinerary.

42:55.473 --> 42:57.140
He went to the library
she's visiting,

42:57.242 --> 42:59.108
the café
she's holding interviews in.

42:59.244 --> 43:01.644
They're looking for
the best moment to approach.

43:07.419 --> 43:09.552
Does anyone have
an aspirin?

43:09.688 --> 43:12.689
<i> [Man speaking indistinctly</i>
<i> on radio]</i>

43:14.659 --> 43:15.725
[Pills rattle]

43:15.860 --> 43:17.927
[Groans]

43:24.235 --> 43:27.236
[Gulps]

43:32.142 --> 43:34.911
[Dogs barking in distance]

43:38.917 --> 43:45.321
♪♪

43:45.457 --> 43:49.025
Litvak: [Speaks Hebrew]

43:49.094 --> 43:51.894
A woman fitting Charlie's
description was seen boarding in

43:52.030 --> 43:53.463
Beirut airport
this morning.

43:53.598 --> 43:55.431
The professor arrives
at the university tomorrow

43:55.567 --> 43:57.500
to scope out the lecture hall
for the evening.

43:57.602 --> 43:59.569
The pieces
are falling into place.

43:59.671 --> 44:00.770
How did she look?

44:00.905 --> 44:02.939
They say strong.

44:03.008 --> 44:05.108
Woman on PA:<i> British Airways</i>
<i> is pleased to announce</i>

44:05.210 --> 44:08.444
<i> the arrival of flight 794</i>
<i> from Paris.</i>

44:08.580 --> 44:17.887
♪♪

44:18.023 --> 44:26.863
♪♪

44:26.965 --> 44:29.799
<i> [Woman on PA</i>
<i> speaking indistinctly]</i>

44:29.901 --> 44:37.073
♪♪

44:37.208 --> 44:43.880
♪♪

44:43.982 --> 44:50.186
♪♪

44:50.321 --> 44:52.755
It's funny.

44:52.891 --> 44:54.590
I've only been gone
a month...

44:54.693 --> 44:57.260
♪♪

44:57.362 --> 44:59.595
And yet it feels like
I've never been here in my life.

44:59.698 --> 45:02.298
♪♪

45:02.434 --> 45:04.400
Helga: Imogen Baastrup?

45:07.272 --> 45:09.138
If you are Afrikaans now,
Charlie,

45:09.240 --> 45:11.140
you must be
a complete fascist.

45:11.242 --> 45:14.444
[Chuckles]

45:14.579 --> 45:17.447
I heard you were wonderful,
you know.

45:17.549 --> 45:19.882
Even Tayeh
was impressed.

45:19.984 --> 45:22.985
[Rain falling]

45:25.590 --> 45:28.558
Have you met him?

45:28.693 --> 45:30.693
Khalil?

45:34.699 --> 45:37.133
No one meets him.

45:37.268 --> 45:40.236
Just Tayeh
and his family.

45:44.275 --> 45:46.008
[Thunder rumbles]

45:46.144 --> 45:48.678
Why don't you come to bed
with Mario and me.

45:51.616 --> 45:54.584
You need to relax so you can
get a good sleep for tomorrow.

45:54.719 --> 45:57.720
You sound like my mum.

45:57.789 --> 46:00.356
You don't like your mother,
Charlie?

46:00.492 --> 46:03.159
Um, well, it's more her
that's not too keen on me,

46:03.294 --> 46:05.561
to be honest.

46:05.697 --> 46:07.296
I'm tired, Helga.

46:07.432 --> 46:10.500
Then we shall
blow them all up.

46:10.635 --> 46:12.869
These English
you hate so much.

46:13.004 --> 46:14.270
Yes?

46:14.405 --> 46:16.372
Yeah, why not?

46:18.343 --> 46:20.943
Why do you think we brought you
back here, Charlie?

46:22.947 --> 46:25.815
[Door closes]

46:30.955 --> 46:34.490
[Keys jingle]

46:34.592 --> 46:37.059
She seemed fine.

46:37.162 --> 46:38.594
She looked cute,
actually.

46:38.696 --> 46:40.696
I think she's playing
a character.

46:48.306 --> 46:51.307
She's saying nothing
because there is nothing to say.

46:51.442 --> 46:54.277
[Helga moaning]

46:54.412 --> 47:03.753
♪♪

47:03.888 --> 47:13.262
♪♪

47:13.364 --> 47:22.738
♪♪

47:22.874 --> 47:32.248
♪♪

47:32.350 --> 47:41.324
♪♪

47:41.426 --> 47:42.525
♪♪

47:42.627 --> 47:44.193
Rachel:<i> Minkel's on her way.</i>

47:44.295 --> 47:47.563
[Van door opens]

47:47.699 --> 47:49.498
[Van door closes]

47:54.372 --> 47:59.208
<i> [Pop music playing on radio]</i>

47:59.310 --> 48:01.577
♪ All that I am ♪

48:01.679 --> 48:03.613
♪ All that I got ♪

48:03.715 --> 48:05.381
♪ All about me ♪

48:05.483 --> 48:09.852
♪♪

48:09.988 --> 48:11.821
-Drinks?
-Ah, yeah.

48:11.956 --> 48:13.623
I'll get them.

48:13.758 --> 48:19.595
♪♪

48:19.731 --> 48:22.331
That'll be £1.10.

48:22.467 --> 48:27.103
♪♪

48:27.171 --> 48:29.272
Two Cokes, please.

48:29.374 --> 48:38.714
♪♪

48:38.850 --> 48:47.823
♪♪

48:47.959 --> 48:50.359
Here's your coffee.

48:50.428 --> 48:51.994
Becker:
And a glass of water, please.

48:52.130 --> 48:58.801
♪♪

48:58.937 --> 49:04.640
♪♪

49:04.742 --> 49:06.442
Thank you.

49:06.544 --> 49:15.885
♪♪

49:16.020 --> 49:25.394
♪♪

49:25.530 --> 49:28.097
-Thank you.
-Thanks.

49:28.199 --> 49:29.332
See you.
-See you.

49:29.434 --> 49:32.735
Minkel:
Both peoples are wounded.

49:32.837 --> 49:36.472
And both peoples have wounded.

49:36.574 --> 49:41.944
I am here to say that it is only
through accepting our own faults

49:42.046 --> 49:45.081
that we might forgive
those faults in --

49:45.149 --> 49:46.949
How is it?
Can you hear me okay?

49:47.085 --> 49:48.884
Yes,
I can hear you fine.

49:58.662 --> 50:02.198
♪♪

50:02.300 --> 50:04.133
-Now.
-No.

50:04.235 --> 50:06.736
You tell me
you know that lady.

50:06.838 --> 50:09.105
[ Scoffs ]
No one can hear us.

50:09.207 --> 50:11.374
♪♪

50:11.509 --> 50:13.609
I think
I know that lady.

50:13.745 --> 50:16.479
Really?
Which lady?

50:23.454 --> 50:25.921
Professor Minkel?

50:26.024 --> 50:27.690
I'm -- I'm so sorry
to trouble you.

50:27.825 --> 50:29.325
My name is
Imogen Baastrup.

50:29.427 --> 50:32.695
I'm a graduate in social studies
from the University of Durban.

50:32.830 --> 50:34.630
I was lucky enough to get
your lecture last year

50:34.732 --> 50:37.833
on minority rights in
racially determined societies.

50:37.969 --> 50:39.168
Anyway, I'm so sorry.

50:39.270 --> 50:40.803
I was wondering if
I could shake your hand?

50:40.938 --> 50:42.838
Professor Minkel's about
to have something to eat.

50:42.940 --> 50:44.306
It's alright.

50:44.409 --> 50:46.509
Thank you so much! How long
are you staying here for?

50:46.611 --> 50:48.611
Just one night,
for the lecture.

50:48.713 --> 50:50.079
And you must come.

50:50.181 --> 50:52.181
Ah, no, I'm so sorry
I can't make it tonight.

50:52.316 --> 50:54.050
I'm actually
visiting my cousin.

50:54.152 --> 50:55.184
Imogen!

50:55.319 --> 50:57.086
Alessio, look!

50:57.155 --> 50:59.555
This is the professor I was
telling you about from Israel.

50:59.690 --> 51:01.023
How do you do.

51:01.125 --> 51:02.691
He's thrilled to meet you,
even if he doesn't seem it.

51:02.827 --> 51:04.193
We both are.

51:04.295 --> 51:06.328
I have not stopped talking
about you for a year.

51:06.431 --> 51:08.597
Anyway,
I really hope tonight

51:08.666 --> 51:09.765
goes brilliantly.
-Thank you.

51:09.867 --> 51:11.434
And it was an honor
to meet you.

51:11.536 --> 51:13.235
-Thank you very much.
-Thank you.

51:13.371 --> 51:15.938
-Bye-bye.
-Bye!

51:16.040 --> 51:17.840
The briefcase.
Into the auditorium.

51:17.975 --> 51:23.045
♪♪

51:23.147 --> 51:24.280
A bomb?

51:24.382 --> 51:26.282
Unclear.

51:26.384 --> 51:27.583
♪♪

51:27.718 --> 51:30.553
[Speaking inaudibly]

51:30.688 --> 51:37.893
♪♪

51:38.029 --> 51:42.231
[Students conversing
indistinctly]

51:42.333 --> 51:43.399
Do we evacuate?

51:43.501 --> 51:44.700
Kurtz:<i> No!</i>

51:44.836 --> 51:45.901
<i> Gadi?</i>

51:46.003 --> 51:47.203
We've got it
out of range.

51:47.338 --> 51:48.838
♪♪

51:48.973 --> 51:51.740
[Breathes deeply]

51:51.809 --> 51:56.846
♪♪

51:56.981 --> 51:58.614
It's light.

51:58.749 --> 52:05.554
♪♪

52:05.690 --> 52:11.494
♪♪

52:11.629 --> 52:13.462
We're clear.

52:13.598 --> 52:16.432
<i> It was a switch.</i>

52:16.534 --> 52:18.801
<i> She'll be coming back</i>
<i> tonight.</i>

52:18.903 --> 52:21.403
-We're closed.
<i> -Return the case.</i>

52:21.506 --> 52:23.405
<i> It'll make</i>
<i> a bigger impact.</i>

52:23.474 --> 52:25.941
<i> At the main event.</i>

52:26.043 --> 52:28.377
Khalil's
building a narrative.

52:28.479 --> 52:29.979
Litvak:<i> They're splitting up,</i>
<i> Marty!</i>

52:30.114 --> 52:32.448
<i>They're splitting up!</i>
<i>We need to follow them!</i>

52:32.550 --> 52:34.984
<i> No.</i>
<i> She'll be back.</i>

52:35.086 --> 52:36.519
<i> This is insane.</i>
<i> How do you know?</i>

52:36.621 --> 52:39.755
<i> Because</i>
<i> that's what I would do.</i>

52:39.891 --> 52:41.724
We're losing them
because you're slut-struck!

52:41.859 --> 52:44.293
We let her go!

52:44.428 --> 52:45.861
Marty!

52:45.963 --> 52:49.331
He will use cut-outs, drag us
around half the country.

52:49.467 --> 52:52.968
Do you think a surveillance team
will survive that unnoticed?

52:53.070 --> 52:54.670
Marty?

52:54.772 --> 52:58.741
♪♪

52:58.843 --> 53:00.309
We don't follow.

53:00.444 --> 53:01.477
♪♪

53:01.612 --> 53:03.078
[Slams receiver]

53:03.214 --> 53:04.513
Daniel:<i> Calling off the pursuit.</i>

53:04.615 --> 53:05.781
<i> Calling off the pursuit.</i>

53:05.917 --> 53:07.416
<i> Return to base.</i>

53:07.552 --> 53:10.986
[Brakes squeak]

53:14.725 --> 53:18.527
[Van door opens]

53:18.629 --> 53:21.130
There was no message
in the cigarette packet.

53:21.265 --> 53:23.832
No contact.

53:23.935 --> 53:26.368
Hmm.

53:28.406 --> 53:30.105
[Switch clicks]

53:36.047 --> 53:38.847
The bracelet
on her right wrist?

53:38.983 --> 53:40.616
A new one.
Thread.

53:40.718 --> 53:42.051
Thread?

53:42.186 --> 53:43.819
She must have lost
the real thing.

53:43.955 --> 53:46.155
You bet all this
on a piece of string?

53:48.025 --> 53:49.124
It was gold and blue.

53:49.227 --> 53:51.560
Come on!

53:51.696 --> 53:55.698
None of his other girls were
brought to Lebanon, after all.

53:55.833 --> 53:59.568
Because of our fiction, it is
an all-or-nothing game now.

53:59.704 --> 54:03.772
She is either a dead body
or a family member.

54:03.874 --> 54:05.241
[Pounds on wall]

54:05.376 --> 54:08.877
[Engine starts]

54:09.013 --> 54:11.480
She wove that bracelet.

54:11.616 --> 54:15.217
That is more precious for us
than gold, than lapis.

54:15.353 --> 54:17.720
Whatever happens,
you should be proud.

54:17.822 --> 54:21.557
♪♪

54:21.626 --> 54:24.860
Drink to our brothers in
the black sands of Palestine.

54:24.962 --> 54:26.662
♪♪

54:26.764 --> 54:28.497
[Glasses clink]

54:28.599 --> 54:32.334
♪♪

54:32.436 --> 54:34.136
What is this?

54:34.272 --> 54:37.106
We made them
in the camps.

54:37.241 --> 54:39.508
It's fashion, Helg.

54:39.644 --> 54:40.809
Radical chic.

54:40.878 --> 54:42.711
[Telephone rings]

54:42.847 --> 54:50.419
♪♪

54:50.554 --> 54:52.721
Yes?

54:52.823 --> 54:54.390
Kurtz: I feel him, Gadi.

54:54.525 --> 54:55.924
Close.

54:56.027 --> 54:57.626
Okay.

54:57.762 --> 55:01.063
I give it another month at
the longest and we'll take him.

55:01.165 --> 55:02.898
I'll let her know.
Yes.

55:03.000 --> 55:04.767
Yes, I'll make sure.

55:04.902 --> 55:06.602
[Receiver clicks]

55:06.704 --> 55:09.805
♪♪

55:09.907 --> 55:11.540
Leave that.

55:11.676 --> 55:14.943
♪♪

55:15.079 --> 55:17.112
Good luck, Charlie.

55:17.248 --> 55:23.052
♪♪

55:23.187 --> 55:26.355
Helga:
Take the green bus seven stops.

55:26.457 --> 55:28.624
Get off and you'll see a church.

55:28.759 --> 55:30.359
A blue van with a yellow ribbon

55:30.494 --> 55:32.695
will take you
to your destination.

55:42.373 --> 55:44.206
[Van door opens]

55:46.644 --> 55:48.644
[Van door closes]

55:48.746 --> 55:51.246
Driver:
We drink to our brothers.

55:51.382 --> 55:53.916
In the black sands
of Palestine.

55:54.051 --> 55:55.984
[Van door opens]

55:56.087 --> 55:59.088
[Birds chirping]

56:16.907 --> 56:18.374
[Parking brake cranks]

56:18.476 --> 56:21.744
[Engine shuts off]

56:21.846 --> 56:26.014
[Van door opens, closes]

56:26.117 --> 56:30.753
♪♪

56:30.855 --> 56:33.222
[Van door opens]

56:33.357 --> 56:41.029
♪♪

56:41.165 --> 56:48.337
♪♪

56:48.472 --> 56:55.677
♪♪

56:55.746 --> 57:02.985
♪♪

57:03.087 --> 57:09.825
♪♪

57:09.960 --> 57:13.028
[Bracelet jingles]

57:13.130 --> 57:20.335
♪♪

57:20.438 --> 57:23.572
[Gasps]

57:23.707 --> 57:26.308
Khalil.

57:26.410 --> 57:33.615
♪♪

57:37.153 --> 57:40.289
My name is Khalil Mater.

57:41.258 --> 57:43.826
Not just a gun trainer,
then?

57:43.928 --> 57:46.929
[Birds cawing]

57:53.504 --> 57:56.505
[Bracelet jingles]

58:21.465 --> 58:24.466
[Rustling]

58:31.375 --> 58:33.642
<i> ["All I Want to Be"</i> plays]

58:33.777 --> 58:36.478
Take off
all your clothes.

58:36.614 --> 58:38.213
♪♪

58:38.315 --> 58:40.749
Apart from
your underwear.

58:41.719 --> 58:43.318
[Sighs]

58:43.420 --> 58:45.354
[Zipper unzips]

58:45.489 --> 58:54.897
♪♪

58:54.999 --> 58:57.900
[Sighs]

58:58.002 --> 59:01.169
Turn, please,
all the way around.

59:01.272 --> 59:09.444
♪♪

59:09.580 --> 59:17.252
♪♪

59:17.388 --> 59:24.593
♪♪

59:24.728 --> 59:27.095
You like
this kind of jewelry?

59:27.231 --> 59:29.565
Not exactly my taste.

59:29.700 --> 59:31.300
Good.

59:31.435 --> 59:32.901
Your actual response.

59:33.037 --> 59:35.938
Not exactly my taste.

59:51.121 --> 59:53.021
You like animals?

59:53.157 --> 59:54.222
Yes.

59:54.358 --> 59:56.191
Did Salim?

59:56.327 --> 59:59.294
Let your instincts
lead you.

59:59.396 --> 1:00:01.597
And take your time.

1:00:01.732 --> 1:00:05.367
It's better to be uncertain
than inconsistent.

1:00:07.037 --> 1:00:09.538
We never
talked about them.

1:00:09.640 --> 1:00:13.842
Not even horses?

1:00:13.978 --> 1:00:17.012
Never, ever
correct yourself.

1:00:17.114 --> 1:00:20.449
Don't remember.

1:00:23.554 --> 1:00:25.253
[Horse whinnies]

1:00:25.389 --> 1:00:28.824
Kurtz: Lord Balfour.

1:00:28.959 --> 1:00:34.062
One signature
and he creates Israel.

1:00:34.164 --> 1:00:37.199
Hubris is always an invitation,
isn't it?

1:00:37.334 --> 1:00:39.835
Picton:
A bloody noose is what it is.

1:00:39.937 --> 1:00:41.937
[Sniffs]

1:00:42.072 --> 1:00:43.839
This insider of yours.

1:00:43.941 --> 1:00:46.074
You're sure
they'll play ball?

1:00:46.210 --> 1:00:47.643
Mm.

1:00:47.745 --> 1:00:51.446
There've been enquiries into
the Professor's schedule, yes?

1:00:51.582 --> 1:00:55.651
Some hack from
a pro-Israeli rag rang.

1:00:55.786 --> 1:00:57.819
Called himself
Hershovitz.

1:00:57.955 --> 1:01:00.422
Wanted to do a piece
on our professor's visit.

1:01:00.557 --> 1:01:03.025
And did the faculty
give this Mr. Hershovitz

1:01:03.160 --> 1:01:04.526
her full schedule?

1:01:04.628 --> 1:01:06.628
Well,
what do you think?

1:01:06.764 --> 1:01:09.531
Has word spread about
the flood in the basement?

1:01:09.633 --> 1:01:11.400
We're not amateurs.

1:01:11.535 --> 1:01:13.568
Oh, well, thank you.

1:01:15.139 --> 1:01:16.838
[Exhales sharply]

1:01:16.940 --> 1:01:18.507
When the dust settles,

1:01:18.609 --> 1:01:22.244
I don't want a whiff of you
or your kind.

1:01:22.312 --> 1:01:26.114
Not in the news, not in the
official reports, not anywhere.

1:01:26.250 --> 1:01:29.851
And all your men
will be issued with these.

1:01:29.953 --> 1:01:32.821
My kind?

1:01:32.923 --> 1:01:36.358
Well, no one lies with a smile
on their face like your lot.

1:01:36.460 --> 1:01:38.427
And for the record,

1:01:38.529 --> 1:01:41.363
I don't like
being handed this on a plate,

1:01:41.432 --> 1:01:43.965
least of all by you.

1:01:50.941 --> 1:01:52.174
I want them back.

1:01:52.309 --> 1:01:53.341
[Door opens]

1:01:53.477 --> 1:01:56.478
[Keys jingle]

1:02:03.220 --> 1:02:06.221
[Fire crackling]

1:02:14.465 --> 1:02:16.631
[Chair scrapes floor]

1:02:21.338 --> 1:02:24.973
Charlie will be
in her element now.

1:02:25.109 --> 1:02:28.744
On stage.

1:02:28.879 --> 1:02:31.246
In her greatest role.

1:02:31.348 --> 1:02:33.648
Too great.

1:02:43.794 --> 1:02:46.128
You think
she's gone over?

1:02:50.934 --> 1:02:56.505
So, my sister says you're ready,
Charlie.

1:02:56.607 --> 1:02:59.508
Are you?

1:02:59.610 --> 1:03:00.742
If she has?

1:03:00.878 --> 1:03:04.679
Then we will do
what is necessary.

1:03:05.682 --> 1:03:09.017
Yes, Gadi.

1:03:09.119 --> 1:03:13.155
What we have done
100 times before.

1:03:13.257 --> 1:03:15.524
Not me.

1:03:15.659 --> 1:03:17.559
Not this time.

1:03:17.661 --> 1:03:20.629
[Clock ticking]

1:03:20.764 --> 1:03:26.635
If she turns,
she turns away.

1:03:26.770 --> 1:03:28.637
♪♪

1:03:28.772 --> 1:03:30.772
[Sighs]

1:03:30.908 --> 1:03:33.708
♪♪

1:03:33.777 --> 1:03:36.244
[Zipper unzips]

1:03:36.346 --> 1:03:37.445
[Chair scrapes floor]

1:03:37.548 --> 1:03:39.848
♪♪

1:03:39.950 --> 1:03:44.920
Do you know why I brought you
back in, Gadi?

1:03:45.055 --> 1:03:50.425
Because you are gifted with
a special, single talent --

1:03:50.494 --> 1:03:52.394
doubt.

1:03:52.496 --> 1:03:54.262
♪♪

1:03:54.398 --> 1:03:56.832
When we have Khalil,

1:03:56.967 --> 1:03:59.568
you will
remember your pride.

1:03:59.670 --> 1:04:01.970
I was happy.

1:04:02.039 --> 1:04:03.839
♪♪

1:04:03.974 --> 1:04:06.374
You were bored.

1:04:06.510 --> 1:04:08.877
Show me the wiring.

1:04:08.979 --> 1:04:11.446
[Footsteps]

1:04:16.253 --> 1:04:18.720
Litvak: Gadi.

1:04:22.192 --> 1:04:25.627
I asked Rachel
about the thread bracelet.

1:04:25.729 --> 1:04:28.496
She told me it was
black and white.

1:04:32.336 --> 1:04:35.003
But I guess it's still
on her right wrist.

1:04:35.138 --> 1:04:38.206
Thank you.

1:04:38.342 --> 1:04:40.542
We have to
use these.

1:04:47.150 --> 1:04:50.252
[Wiring crinkling]

1:04:50.354 --> 1:04:53.021
What do you think of
this Professor Minkel?

1:04:54.825 --> 1:04:57.158
She wants peace.

1:04:57.261 --> 1:05:00.762
I think
she's a good person.

1:05:00.864 --> 1:05:04.165
Maybe she is.

1:05:06.003 --> 1:05:08.270
So why kill her?

1:05:08.372 --> 1:05:11.006
Because her hope
is a fantasy.

1:05:11.141 --> 1:05:13.174
[Fire crackling]

1:05:17.681 --> 1:05:20.115
I told Salim many times

1:05:20.250 --> 1:05:21.549
a woman cannot be trusted

1:05:21.685 --> 1:05:23.952
just because
you go to bed with her.

1:05:24.087 --> 1:05:25.921
And what about a man?

1:05:26.056 --> 1:05:27.956
A man cannot be trusted
ever.

1:05:33.764 --> 1:05:36.364
Why did he
tell you my name?

1:05:36.466 --> 1:05:38.199
[Breathes deeply]

1:05:38.302 --> 1:05:40.135
Because he loved me.

1:05:40.237 --> 1:05:43.605
And he loved you.

1:05:47.577 --> 1:05:49.611
I had three brothers,
you know.

1:05:49.746 --> 1:05:52.347
Now I have none.

1:05:52.482 --> 1:05:54.783
You have a family?

1:05:57.020 --> 1:05:58.153
You know.

1:05:58.288 --> 1:06:01.156
Do this just once,

1:06:01.291 --> 1:06:04.292
and you will always
have one.

1:06:07.064 --> 1:06:09.097
How did it feel, please,
to kill the American traitor?

1:06:09.232 --> 1:06:10.298
I didn't kill him.

1:06:10.434 --> 1:06:12.267
You did.

1:06:15.005 --> 1:06:16.938
It was horrible.

1:06:17.040 --> 1:06:19.441
Good.

1:06:19.576 --> 1:06:22.544
If a man's life
is not significant,

1:06:22.612 --> 1:06:24.546
what is the point
in taking it?

1:06:24.648 --> 1:06:26.681
[Birds chirping]

1:06:42.766 --> 1:06:46.368
[Yawns]

1:06:46.470 --> 1:06:48.737
I am boring you?

1:06:48.839 --> 1:06:51.806
No. No. Sorry.

1:06:51.942 --> 1:06:55.243
It's nerves.

1:06:55.379 --> 1:06:59.047
It's the same with the theater
when I'm about to go on.

1:06:59.182 --> 1:07:01.282
Feel like I could sleep
for 100 years.

1:07:01.385 --> 1:07:02.751
[Yawns]

1:07:02.853 --> 1:07:04.886
[Chuckles]

1:07:14.031 --> 1:07:18.133
I feel that the Israelis
are close, you know?

1:07:18.268 --> 1:07:21.236
All the time.

1:07:21.304 --> 1:07:25.840
I imagine they have someone
moving the pieces to get to me,

1:07:25.976 --> 1:07:28.843
someone whose mind has been
carved away to obsession

1:07:28.945 --> 1:07:31.846
by his
decades of battle.

1:07:31.948 --> 1:07:37.018
He knows me,
but I don't know him.

1:07:39.423 --> 1:07:43.091
In my head,
I've made him into a devil,

1:07:43.193 --> 1:07:46.761
a Dybbuk from their texts.

1:07:46.897 --> 1:07:50.965
Because without that,
I wouldn't be afraid of him.

1:07:53.670 --> 1:07:54.702
[Sighs] Listen to me.

1:07:54.838 --> 1:07:55.970
I'm going on
like an old man.

1:07:56.073 --> 1:07:58.640
[Chuckles]

1:08:02.579 --> 1:08:04.546
Did Salim like horses?

1:08:04.648 --> 1:08:06.314
They terrified him.

1:08:06.416 --> 1:08:08.650
Our grandfather had one.

1:08:08.752 --> 1:08:10.351
He had to sell it.

1:08:10.454 --> 1:08:12.720
Why?

1:08:12.823 --> 1:08:14.355
To buy a gun.

1:08:21.198 --> 1:08:25.900
[Electricity humming]

1:08:26.870 --> 1:08:29.370
You're too young
to be a widow.

1:08:33.677 --> 1:08:37.579
Professor Minkel
begins speaking at 5:30.

1:08:37.714 --> 1:08:39.747
I shall set it for 5:30.

1:08:39.883 --> 1:08:41.916
And the hall
will be full.

1:08:44.254 --> 1:08:47.021
Yes.

1:08:47.124 --> 1:08:49.791
But maybe she will
try the latch before.

1:08:49.893 --> 1:08:52.393
I have put a trigger there,
too.

1:08:52.462 --> 1:08:54.596
If the briefcase opens,

1:08:54.698 --> 1:08:58.333
it will explode
instantly.

1:08:58.435 --> 1:09:01.402
Always two things.

1:09:01.538 --> 1:09:04.139
Where did you
hear this?

1:09:04.274 --> 1:09:06.374
From Salim.

1:09:06.510 --> 1:09:09.344
"Two bullets.

1:09:09.446 --> 1:09:12.180
In case the world's
still alive."

1:09:12.282 --> 1:09:19.087
♪♪

1:09:19.222 --> 1:09:21.723
Salim was a kid.

1:09:21.858 --> 1:09:24.092
♪♪

1:09:24.194 --> 1:09:29.664
Too much with women, cars,
poetry, watches.

1:09:29.799 --> 1:09:32.066
We're not the same thing,
you know.

1:09:32.202 --> 1:09:33.434
♪♪

1:09:33.570 --> 1:09:35.537
Women and cars.

1:09:35.605 --> 1:09:37.605
[Chuckles]

1:09:37.741 --> 1:09:45.113
♪♪

1:09:45.248 --> 1:09:46.481
[Door opens]

1:09:54.157 --> 1:09:55.790
Show me your hand,
please.

1:10:03.934 --> 1:10:05.800
You don't have to do this,
Charlie.

1:10:05.902 --> 1:10:08.803
You can go back to your old life
now if you want.

1:10:08.939 --> 1:10:11.039
I won't come after you.

1:10:11.174 --> 1:10:15.109
[Sighs]

1:10:23.553 --> 1:10:25.019
[Gate opens]

1:10:29.025 --> 1:10:30.391
[Briefcase unlatches]

1:10:32.529 --> 1:10:33.628
[Clock windi]

1:10:33.730 --> 1:10:35.697
Khalil:
The clock is ticking.

1:10:41.404 --> 1:10:44.405
Will I see you again?

1:10:44.541 --> 1:10:48.343
That cannot happen.

1:10:51.681 --> 1:10:53.681
Mm.

1:11:02.125 --> 1:11:04.292
Wish me luck.

1:11:07.197 --> 1:11:09.864
[Inhales deeply]

1:11:09.966 --> 1:11:12.967
[Indistinct shouting]

1:11:24.781 --> 1:11:28.616
Peace is more popular
than your lot thought.

1:11:28.752 --> 1:11:31.352
The British
always have the solution

1:11:31.488 --> 1:11:34.522
to other countries'
problems.

1:11:34.658 --> 1:11:38.459
Perhaps you should try listening
for once.

1:11:39.729 --> 1:11:43.131
[Engine idling]

1:11:43.266 --> 1:11:46.034
Oi, you can't stop here.
Move on.

1:11:46.136 --> 1:11:47.669
Charlie: All right, all right.
Okay. Sorry.

1:11:47.804 --> 1:11:49.270
We're going.

1:11:49.406 --> 1:11:57.979
♪♪

1:11:58.081 --> 1:11:59.847
[Brakes squeak]

1:11:59.983 --> 1:12:03.384
[Car door opens]

1:12:03.520 --> 1:12:05.353
[Camera shutter clicking]

1:12:05.488 --> 1:12:07.889
[Indistinct conversations]

1:12:07.991 --> 1:12:10.291
♪♪

1:12:10.427 --> 1:12:13.061
This way, sir. This way.

1:12:13.163 --> 1:12:15.129
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

1:12:15.265 --> 1:12:23.104
♪♪

1:12:23.239 --> 1:12:24.405
[South African accent]
Excuse me.

1:12:24.474 --> 1:12:25.573
I have Professor Minkel's
briefcase.

1:12:25.675 --> 1:12:26.841
Ticket?

1:12:26.976 --> 1:12:28.076
I-I don't have one.

1:12:28.178 --> 1:12:29.544
This belongs to
Professor Minkel.

1:12:29.646 --> 1:12:31.079
There was a mix-up.
We swapped by mistake.

1:12:31.214 --> 1:12:33.715
Oh, side entrance.

1:12:33.817 --> 1:12:34.949
Who's in charge
of security here?

1:12:35.051 --> 1:12:36.150
John Kemp.

1:12:36.219 --> 1:12:38.586
John Kemp.
Okay. Thank you.

1:12:38.722 --> 1:12:40.621
Ambassador,
how nice to meet you.

1:12:40.757 --> 1:12:43.725
♪♪

1:12:43.860 --> 1:12:45.360
Excuse me.
Excuse me. Hi.

1:12:45.495 --> 1:12:47.562
The lecture's about to begin.
No one's coming in this way.

1:12:47.664 --> 1:12:48.830
I know, I know,
but someone needs to

1:12:48.932 --> 1:12:50.398
take this up
to Professor Minkel.

1:12:50.500 --> 1:12:52.166
There's been a mix-up.
I took hers by mistake,

1:12:52.302 --> 1:12:55.303
and it's probably got her speech
in here.

1:12:55.438 --> 1:12:56.871
Please, please!

1:12:57.006 --> 1:12:58.740
John Kemp on the front doors
said that you'd take it in.

1:12:58.842 --> 1:13:00.842
He said it was fine.

1:13:00.977 --> 1:13:03.044
Make it quick, okay?

1:13:03.179 --> 1:13:04.245
-[Sighs] Thank you.
-Sixth floor.

1:13:04.381 --> 1:13:05.880
Thank you, thank you.

1:13:06.015 --> 1:13:12.553
♪♪

1:13:12.655 --> 1:13:14.222
I know.

1:13:14.357 --> 1:13:16.057
[Normal voice]
The timer's set for 5:30,

1:13:16.159 --> 1:13:17.725
and there's a trigger
on the latch, too.

1:13:17.827 --> 1:13:20.561
Come.

1:13:25.468 --> 1:13:27.668
Gadi. Gadi.

1:13:29.038 --> 1:13:31.239
Trust me.

1:13:36.145 --> 1:13:37.945
[Doors thud]

1:13:42.852 --> 1:13:45.019
What the hell?

1:13:46.389 --> 1:13:48.222
Play the scene,
Charlie.

1:13:48.358 --> 1:13:50.425
The bomb,
it's set for 5:30.

1:13:50.560 --> 1:13:52.059
[Watch ticking]

1:13:52.162 --> 1:13:53.494
♪♪

1:13:53.596 --> 1:13:56.164
Play the scene.

1:13:56.299 --> 1:13:58.866
♪♪

1:13:58.968 --> 1:14:00.301
What?

1:14:00.437 --> 1:14:03.704
Charmian Ross?
You sneaky shit.

1:14:03.840 --> 1:14:04.939
I'll take that.

1:14:05.074 --> 1:14:07.475
No.

1:14:07.610 --> 1:14:10.812
I'm so sorry
for the inconvenience.

1:14:10.880 --> 1:14:12.346
I think
our cases got switched.

1:14:12.449 --> 1:14:13.614
Thank God.

1:14:13.716 --> 1:14:16.017
I would have had to
make it all up.

1:14:16.152 --> 1:14:18.386
This is yours.

1:14:18.521 --> 1:14:21.355
I'm so glad I caught you
before you went on.

1:14:21.458 --> 1:14:22.824
Best of luck
with the speech.

1:14:22.959 --> 1:14:24.292
Thank you.

1:14:24.394 --> 1:14:26.160
Now?

1:14:26.296 --> 1:14:27.995
Yes.

1:14:28.097 --> 1:14:30.698
♪♪

1:14:30.800 --> 1:14:32.633
[Exhales sharply]

1:14:32.735 --> 1:14:33.801
♪♪

1:14:33.903 --> 1:14:35.336
[Crate opens]

1:14:35.472 --> 1:14:41.676
♪♪

1:14:41.811 --> 1:14:47.081
♪♪

1:14:47.217 --> 1:14:49.350
[Thumps crate]
-Out.

1:14:49.452 --> 1:14:52.253
Meadows, look after the ladies.
-Yes, sir.

1:14:52.388 --> 1:14:54.155
What the hell
are you playing at?

1:14:54.257 --> 1:14:57.625
What does it matter to you?
We run this.

1:14:57.760 --> 1:15:02.697
♪♪

1:15:02.799 --> 1:15:05.266
Bravissimo, Charlie.
Now --

1:15:05.335 --> 1:15:06.767
I met Khalil.

1:15:06.903 --> 1:15:08.703
What?

1:15:08.771 --> 1:15:11.305
And he wants
to see me again.

1:15:11.441 --> 1:15:13.541
How can you be so sure?

1:15:13.676 --> 1:15:16.511
Because he's falling in love
with me.

1:15:16.646 --> 1:15:18.012
♪♪

1:15:18.114 --> 1:15:20.248
I see.

1:15:20.383 --> 1:15:22.283
Well, thank you.

1:15:22.418 --> 1:15:24.886
Thank you for telling me that,
Charlie.

1:15:25.021 --> 1:15:27.288
♪♪

1:15:27.423 --> 1:15:29.190
Come on. Come on.

1:15:29.325 --> 1:15:33.194
All of you.

1:15:33.329 --> 1:15:37.031
Gadi,
this changes everything.

1:15:37.133 --> 1:15:40.334
We follow her tonight.

1:15:40.403 --> 1:15:42.570
And take him,
but don't kill him.

1:15:42.672 --> 1:15:46.574
No, we let them run.

1:15:46.709 --> 1:15:51.245
Deep cover.
We will have her by his side

1:15:51.314 --> 1:15:53.548
as he becomes the leader
of his people.

1:15:53.683 --> 1:15:54.749
That could take years.

1:15:54.851 --> 1:15:56.250
No,
can't you see, Gadi?

1:15:56.386 --> 1:15:59.954
Can't you see
what a big future he has?

1:16:00.056 --> 1:16:03.925
We could pull in every contact,
every cell.

1:16:04.027 --> 1:16:05.760
No,
you can't do that to her.

1:16:05.895 --> 1:16:08.396
Give her
the location transmitter,

1:16:08.498 --> 1:16:10.131
tell her to
remove the batteries.

1:16:10.233 --> 1:16:12.533
If she is in real danger
tonight,

1:16:12.669 --> 1:16:16.404
we will come in if he's not
so loving as she thinks,

1:16:16.539 --> 1:16:22.543
but otherwise,
we leave her.

1:16:22.679 --> 1:16:27.014
♪♪

1:16:27.116 --> 1:16:29.650
Charlie,
Gadi will brief you.

1:16:29.786 --> 1:16:37.825
♪♪

1:16:37.961 --> 1:16:45.099
♪♪

1:16:45.201 --> 1:16:47.535
The second you leave here,
you're back in play.

1:16:47.637 --> 1:16:50.771
Forget everything you just saw
but the fiction.

1:16:53.710 --> 1:16:55.977
We built in a location
transmitter now.

1:16:56.112 --> 1:16:57.712
You'll be listening?

1:16:57.847 --> 1:16:59.747
We can't be
that close.

1:16:59.882 --> 1:17:01.949
We need to
follow you unseen.

1:17:02.085 --> 1:17:04.619
You take the batteries out,
I'll come running.

1:17:04.721 --> 1:17:06.420
Cutting the signal
will be the signal.

1:17:06.522 --> 1:17:07.622
Okay?

1:17:07.724 --> 1:17:09.757
Signal for what?

1:17:12.395 --> 1:17:14.061
Come on!

1:17:14.197 --> 1:17:18.132
What did Marty
say in there?

1:17:18.234 --> 1:17:20.368
The signal for what?

1:17:20.436 --> 1:17:22.737
That he's asleep.

1:17:22.839 --> 1:17:24.939
Call me in
as soon as he's vulnerable.

1:17:25.074 --> 1:17:28.009
Put him at ease.

1:17:28.144 --> 1:17:30.978
Put him at ease?

1:17:31.114 --> 1:17:33.581
Charlie.

1:17:35.318 --> 1:17:36.450
How?

1:17:36.552 --> 1:17:38.552
Trust me.

1:17:38.688 --> 1:17:40.221
It's the only way
we can finish this.

1:17:40.289 --> 1:17:42.490
You want me
to sleep with him?

1:17:42.625 --> 1:17:45.059
Go on. Say it!

1:17:46.195 --> 1:17:49.096
Give me an order
for once.

1:17:49.198 --> 1:17:51.065
You need to
keep a clear head.

1:17:51.200 --> 1:17:52.533
Sir.
Head clear, sir.

1:17:52.635 --> 1:17:55.169
Legs open, sir.

1:17:58.207 --> 1:18:00.675
What will you do
with him?

1:18:02.512 --> 1:18:04.879
Will you kill him?

1:18:14.023 --> 1:18:16.090
He's beautiful.

1:18:19.028 --> 1:18:21.228
Did you know that?

1:18:23.032 --> 1:18:31.605
♪♪

1:18:31.741 --> 1:18:39.346
♪♪

1:18:39.482 --> 1:18:41.949
[Engine revs]

1:18:42.085 --> 1:18:47.755
♪♪

1:18:47.890 --> 1:18:49.123
What took you so long?

1:18:49.225 --> 1:18:50.791
Nothing!

1:18:50.893 --> 1:18:53.828
♪♪

1:18:53.930 --> 1:18:55.863
Just some pig. Go.

1:18:55.998 --> 1:19:03.537
♪♪

1:19:03.606 --> 1:19:10.344
♪♪

1:19:10.480 --> 1:19:13.914
[Explosion]

1:19:14.016 --> 1:19:17.051
[Breathing echoing]

1:19:23.693 --> 1:19:33.067
♪♪

1:19:33.202 --> 1:19:34.668
[Screaming]

1:19:34.804 --> 1:19:36.237
[Sirens wailing]

1:19:36.372 --> 1:19:38.873
[Alarm ringing]

1:19:39.008 --> 1:19:41.842
[Indistinct shouting]

1:19:41.978 --> 1:19:49.650
♪♪

1:19:49.752 --> 1:19:51.418
Woman: This way.

1:19:51.554 --> 1:19:53.454
[Woman coughing]

1:19:53.556 --> 1:19:56.423
[Shouting continues]

1:19:56.526 --> 1:20:03.631
♪♪

1:20:03.699 --> 1:20:10.371
♪♪

1:20:10.473 --> 1:20:15.810
♪♪

1:20:18.914 --> 1:20:20.414
Follow that lane.

1:20:20.516 --> 1:20:22.449
Look for the first house
on your left.

1:20:22.552 --> 1:20:23.751
[Engine revving]

1:20:34.397 --> 1:20:36.730
[Monitor beeping]

1:20:39.769 --> 1:20:41.869
Slow down.
She's on foot.

1:20:42.004 --> 1:20:45.005
[Birds chirping]

1:21:30.386 --> 1:21:33.387
[Man breathing heavily]

1:21:37.760 --> 1:21:39.827
[Keys jingle]

1:21:41.697 --> 1:21:43.664
How was it?

1:21:43.799 --> 1:21:46.267
Take me through it,
please.

1:21:46.369 --> 1:21:49.536
They -- They --
They wanted a ticket.

1:21:49.639 --> 1:21:51.272
So I-I had to go through
a side door.

1:21:51.407 --> 1:21:52.439
Police?

1:21:52.575 --> 1:21:54.174
Two,
but one tried to stop me.

1:21:54.277 --> 1:21:57.077
They made me take it in,
and I ran down a corridor.

1:21:57.213 --> 1:21:59.179
You gave it to her
yourself?

1:21:59.315 --> 1:22:00.981
Uh-huh. She was backstage
in a room, nervous.

1:22:01.117 --> 1:22:04.385
She had -- had a bead of sweat
on her brow.

1:22:04.520 --> 1:22:06.987
Because of the speech?

1:22:07.089 --> 1:22:10.157
She said, "Thank God," she'd
have had to make it up herself.

1:22:10.293 --> 1:22:14.461
What happened to her?

1:22:14.563 --> 1:22:16.964
She died.

1:22:19.402 --> 1:22:21.402
Ah.

1:22:21.671 --> 1:22:23.971
[Van approaching]

1:22:33.449 --> 1:22:41.188
♪♪

1:22:41.324 --> 1:22:45.092
[Brakes squeak,
engine shuts off]

1:22:45.194 --> 1:22:53.300
♪♪

1:22:53.436 --> 1:23:01.108
♪♪

1:23:01.210 --> 1:23:08.849
♪♪

1:23:08.985 --> 1:23:15.723
♪♪

1:23:15.825 --> 1:23:16.924
She's moved.

1:23:17.026 --> 1:23:22.763
♪♪

1:23:22.898 --> 1:23:24.698
Changing observation point.

1:23:24.834 --> 1:23:28.669
♪♪

1:23:28.771 --> 1:23:30.504
Reporter:<i> I'm at the scene</i>
<i> of the gruesome attack</i>

1:23:30.639 --> 1:23:32.306
<i> at the Polytechnic</i>
<i> of Greater London,</i>

1:23:32.408 --> 1:23:34.341
<i> and I have with me</i>
<i> Chief Inspector Picton.</i>

1:23:34.477 --> 1:23:36.677
Picton:<i> We're looking for</i>
<i>one woman in particular.</i>

1:23:36.812 --> 1:23:38.345
<i> She was wearing a duffel coat.</i>

1:23:38.447 --> 1:23:40.347
<i> A dark wig</i>
<i>discarded at the scene</i>

1:23:40.449 --> 1:23:42.349
<i> suggests that</i>
<i>the girl was blonde.</i>

1:23:42.451 --> 1:23:45.085
<i>She was of medium build,</i>
<i>wearing spectacles,</i>

1:23:45.187 --> 1:23:47.955
<i> and, um, speaking with</i>
<i>a South African accent,</i>

1:23:48.057 --> 1:23:49.890
<i>which is probably fake.</i>

1:23:49.992 --> 1:23:52.192
Bastard.

1:23:52.328 --> 1:23:55.396
Did you really
leave the wig?

1:23:55.498 --> 1:23:58.766
I'm sorry.

1:23:58.901 --> 1:24:00.734
You are a little bit at risk,
it seems.

1:24:00.870 --> 1:24:03.170
<i> ...treated for wounds,</i>
<i> and his family is offering --</i>

1:24:03.305 --> 1:24:05.806
[Television turns off]

1:24:09.311 --> 1:24:12.913
[Radio clicks]

1:24:13.015 --> 1:24:15.816
<i> ["Things Ain't What</i>
<i> They Used to Be"</i> plays]

1:24:15.951 --> 1:24:23.957
♪♪

1:24:24.026 --> 1:24:25.926
[Chair scrapes floor]

1:24:26.028 --> 1:24:31.498
♪♪

1:24:31.600 --> 1:24:36.270
♪♪

1:24:39.408 --> 1:24:42.609
♪♪

1:24:42.711 --> 1:24:44.478
I think
we deserve a drink.

1:24:44.613 --> 1:24:46.747
[Chuckles]

1:24:46.882 --> 1:24:49.683
God, yes,
I'm dying for one.

1:24:49.819 --> 1:24:57.524
♪♪

1:24:57.626 --> 1:24:59.960
[Monitor beeping]

1:25:00.062 --> 1:25:02.563
[Slurps]

1:25:10.138 --> 1:25:13.407
Have you ever fished
in the dark, Charlie,

1:25:13.509 --> 1:25:16.276
with a lamp, catching the fish
with your hands?

1:25:16.345 --> 1:25:18.345
With my hands?

1:25:18.481 --> 1:25:21.181
No.

1:25:21.317 --> 1:25:25.686
♪♪

1:25:25.821 --> 1:25:27.221
I took these two boys
on a mission

1:25:27.323 --> 1:25:29.723
into the Galilee long ago.

1:25:29.859 --> 1:25:32.292
We were crossing the sea
in a rowing boat

1:25:32.428 --> 1:25:34.261
and the night
was so beautiful

1:25:34.396 --> 1:25:37.164
that they lost all sense
of what they had come for.

1:25:37.266 --> 1:25:39.099
And what did you do?

1:25:39.201 --> 1:25:40.868
I let them fish.

1:25:41.003 --> 1:25:42.636
[Chuckles]

1:25:42.771 --> 1:25:44.838
♪♪

1:25:44.940 --> 1:25:46.607
Was that Salim?

1:25:46.742 --> 1:25:49.076
♪♪

1:25:49.178 --> 1:25:51.512
I completed the mission
alone.

1:25:51.614 --> 1:25:53.914
♪♪

1:25:57.486 --> 1:25:58.552
♪♪

1:25:58.687 --> 1:26:00.154
I'm tired.

1:26:00.289 --> 1:26:02.022
♪♪

1:26:02.091 --> 1:26:03.457
Aren't you?

1:26:03.559 --> 1:26:05.425
♪♪

1:26:05.494 --> 1:26:07.861
I don't sleep.

1:26:07.963 --> 1:26:11.098
[Sighs]

1:26:11.233 --> 1:26:13.400
[Lighter clicking]

1:26:13.502 --> 1:26:20.541
♪♪

1:26:20.643 --> 1:26:27.548
♪♪

1:26:27.683 --> 1:26:34.054
♪♪

1:26:34.123 --> 1:26:36.056
In your letters to my brother,
you said,

1:26:36.158 --> 1:26:39.626
"Your head on our pillow
and your gun beneath it."

1:26:39.728 --> 1:26:43.730
Yeah.

1:26:43.866 --> 1:26:46.767
He made me sleep with your gun
under our pillow.

1:26:46.869 --> 1:26:48.569
[Exhales sharply]

1:26:48.671 --> 1:26:50.871
Only cowboys
sleep like that.

1:26:50.973 --> 1:26:53.840
You must keep it at your side
where your hand is.

1:26:53.943 --> 1:26:56.276
I made him promise.

1:26:56.412 --> 1:26:59.947
♪♪

1:27:00.082 --> 1:27:02.849
Maybe he liked
breaking your promises.

1:27:02.952 --> 1:27:04.585
And look at him now.

1:27:04.720 --> 1:27:10.090
♪♪

1:27:10.192 --> 1:27:12.693
[Glass thuds]

1:27:12.828 --> 1:27:19.833
♪♪

1:27:19.902 --> 1:27:21.468
Come here.

1:27:21.604 --> 1:27:24.238
No.

1:27:24.373 --> 1:27:27.374
♪♪

1:27:27.476 --> 1:27:29.876
Please.

1:27:30.012 --> 1:27:36.917
♪♪

1:27:37.019 --> 1:27:42.556
♪♪

1:27:42.658 --> 1:27:44.458
It hurt you so much,
killing these people?

1:27:44.560 --> 1:27:46.693
No.

1:27:46.829 --> 1:27:48.695
No.
They're murderers.

1:27:48.797 --> 1:27:49.896
They're -- They're pigs.

1:27:50.032 --> 1:27:52.866
Shh.

1:27:53.002 --> 1:27:56.336
You're trying too hard
to hate them.

1:27:56.472 --> 1:28:03.477
♪♪

1:28:03.612 --> 1:28:10.150
♪♪

1:28:10.252 --> 1:28:16.156
♪♪

1:28:16.292 --> 1:28:18.292
Again.

1:28:18.394 --> 1:28:19.860
♪♪

1:28:19.928 --> 1:28:22.462
[Sighs]

1:28:35.611 --> 1:28:43.517
♪♪

1:28:43.619 --> 1:28:51.091
♪♪

1:28:51.193 --> 1:28:57.864
♪♪

1:28:57.966 --> 1:29:00.033
Stop.

1:29:00.135 --> 1:29:04.604
♪♪

1:29:04.707 --> 1:29:06.807
You don't have to do this,
Charlie.

1:29:06.909 --> 1:29:16.016
♪♪

1:29:16.151 --> 1:29:24.758
♪♪

1:29:24.893 --> 1:29:33.467
♪♪

1:29:33.569 --> 1:29:42.209
♪♪

1:29:42.311 --> 1:29:50.951
♪♪

1:29:51.053 --> 1:29:59.693
♪♪

1:29:59.795 --> 1:30:08.368
♪♪

1:30:08.504 --> 1:30:17.110
♪♪

1:30:17.246 --> 1:30:25.252
♪♪

1:30:25.387 --> 1:30:26.620
[Exhales sharply]

1:30:26.755 --> 1:30:35.796
♪♪

1:30:35.931 --> 1:30:44.070
♪♪

1:30:44.173 --> 1:30:47.040
[Panting]

1:30:47.142 --> 1:30:54.281
♪♪

1:30:54.416 --> 1:31:00.554
♪♪

1:31:00.656 --> 1:31:03.490
[Both moaning]

1:31:03.592 --> 1:31:12.966
♪♪

1:31:13.101 --> 1:31:21.107
♪♪

1:31:21.243 --> 1:31:24.044
[Monitor beeping]

1:31:36.724 --> 1:31:38.658
[Breathing deeply]

1:31:38.760 --> 1:31:45.532
<i> [Radio playing indistinctly]</i>

1:31:45.667 --> 1:31:48.235
Any signs
of them leaving?

1:31:48.370 --> 1:31:49.936
No.

1:31:50.038 --> 1:31:53.039
<i> Remember,</i>
<i> we let them run.</i>

1:31:53.175 --> 1:31:59.145
We don't move unless
she calls us in, Gadi.

1:32:04.186 --> 1:32:07.187
[Beeping]

1:32:11.693 --> 1:32:14.694
<i> [Radio playing indistinctly]</i>

1:32:17.099 --> 1:32:19.399
Where are you going?

1:32:19.501 --> 1:32:23.303
I'm gonna
go turn that off.

1:32:23.438 --> 1:32:25.672
I don't want to
hear that now.

1:32:25.807 --> 1:32:30.810
[Breathing deeply]

1:32:52.801 --> 1:32:54.234
Reporter:
<i> ...number of casualties,</i>

1:32:54.336 --> 1:32:57.537
<i> but it is expected to be</i>
<i> a dozen, if not more.</i>

1:32:57.673 --> 1:33:00.707
<i> No group has taken</i>
<i> responsibility for the attack,</i>

1:33:00.842 --> 1:33:01.875
<i> but as the Israelis --</i>

1:33:02.010 --> 1:33:03.643
[Radio turns off]

1:33:30.238 --> 1:33:32.305
[Beeping continues]

1:33:44.753 --> 1:33:46.953
[Clattering]

1:33:55.197 --> 1:33:57.764
[Beeping continues]

1:33:57.899 --> 1:34:00.900
[Breathing deeply]

1:34:16.551 --> 1:34:18.785
How did you
pick up this?

1:34:18.854 --> 1:34:21.054
I didn't.

1:34:21.189 --> 1:34:24.124
It was the Zionists.

1:34:27.663 --> 1:34:30.597
Jordanians.

1:34:32.768 --> 1:34:34.968
Syrians.

1:34:46.081 --> 1:34:50.417
♪♪

1:34:50.485 --> 1:34:52.886
Our friends are here.

1:34:52.988 --> 1:34:54.721
♪♪

1:34:54.823 --> 1:34:56.756
Picton's men --
they followed us.

1:34:56.858 --> 1:34:59.325
They blocked the perimeter.
Nothing's coming in or out.

1:34:59.428 --> 1:35:01.027
♪♪

1:35:01.163 --> 1:35:02.896
[Groans]

1:35:02.998 --> 1:35:04.230
They'll ruin everything.

1:35:04.366 --> 1:35:06.099
Tell them
to open it back up.

1:35:06.201 --> 1:35:08.301
Everything
must play as usual.

1:35:08.403 --> 1:35:10.003
Understood.

1:35:10.138 --> 1:35:19.112
♪♪

1:35:19.247 --> 1:35:27.954
♪♪

1:35:28.056 --> 1:35:36.296
♪♪

1:35:36.398 --> 1:35:38.331
[Paper rustles]

1:35:38.433 --> 1:35:42.669
♪♪

1:35:42.771 --> 1:35:44.671
[Watch ticking]

1:35:44.740 --> 1:35:51.211
♪♪

1:35:51.313 --> 1:35:56.816
♪♪

1:35:56.885 --> 1:35:59.252
Charlie: What --
What is it?

1:35:59.387 --> 1:36:02.989
♪♪

1:36:03.091 --> 1:36:05.225
The milkman
comes every morning.

1:36:05.327 --> 1:36:07.227
Yeah, it's --
it's too early.

1:36:07.362 --> 1:36:10.396
No.
6:15 every day.

1:36:10.499 --> 1:36:13.433
Maybe
he's running late?

1:36:13.535 --> 1:36:16.035
Why would he
be late?

1:36:16.138 --> 1:36:18.505
Why do you
provide excuses?

1:36:18.607 --> 1:36:20.173
I'm not.

1:36:20.308 --> 1:36:22.575
I'm just --
I'm trying to comfort you.

1:36:22.711 --> 1:36:24.844
Why would you wish
to comfort me?

1:36:24.913 --> 1:36:27.247
Why would you
be frightened for me?

1:36:27.349 --> 1:36:32.919
♪♪

1:36:33.054 --> 1:36:37.657
♪♪

1:36:37.793 --> 1:36:39.993
What guilt
is in your mind?

1:36:40.128 --> 1:36:43.830
[Breathing heavily]

1:36:43.965 --> 1:36:46.366
♪♪

1:36:46.501 --> 1:36:49.636
Turn it on,
your little radio.

1:36:49.771 --> 1:36:51.871
Uh --
[Exhales sharply]

1:36:51.973 --> 1:36:54.007
Turn it on, please.

1:37:00.215 --> 1:37:05.451
[Rustling]

1:37:05.587 --> 1:37:07.086
<i> ["Final Solution"</i> plays]

1:37:07.222 --> 1:37:08.655
♪<i> Won't approve of</i>
<i> my strange kind of wit</i> ♪

1:37:08.790 --> 1:37:09.856
See?

1:37:09.991 --> 1:37:13.026
♪♪

1:37:13.161 --> 1:37:17.530
♪<i> I get so excited,</i>
<i> I always gotta lose it</i> ♪

1:37:17.632 --> 1:37:20.333
♪<i> Man, that sent me off,</i>
<i> made me take the cure</i> ♪

1:37:20.435 --> 1:37:22.068
Bring it to me.

1:37:22.170 --> 1:37:24.804
♪<i> D-Don't need a cure,</i>
<i> d-don't need a cure</i> ♪

1:37:24.940 --> 1:37:26.573
♪<i> D-Don't need a cure</i> ♪

1:37:26.708 --> 1:37:28.675
♪<i> Need a final solution</i> ♪

1:37:28.777 --> 1:37:30.610
♪<i> I don't need a cure</i> ♪

1:37:30.712 --> 1:37:32.645
Since last afternoon,

1:37:32.747 --> 1:37:34.314
you haven't had much time
to yourself.

1:37:34.449 --> 1:37:35.915
None.

1:37:36.051 --> 1:37:38.885
Then why
is this radio working?

1:37:39.020 --> 1:37:40.854
♪♪

1:37:58.540 --> 1:38:01.741
These radios,
they run on batteries, yes?

1:38:01.877 --> 1:38:03.376
Yes, Khalil.

1:38:03.511 --> 1:38:06.746
♪<i> Buy me a ticket</i>
<i> to a sonic reduction</i> ♪

1:38:06.882 --> 1:38:08.882
Wait.

1:38:09.017 --> 1:38:11.651
♪♪

1:38:11.786 --> 1:38:13.620
Why?

1:38:13.688 --> 1:38:15.889
♪<i> Guitars gonna sound like</i>
<i> a nuclear destruction</i> ♪

1:38:16.024 --> 1:38:17.824
Turn, please.

1:38:17.959 --> 1:38:19.959
All the way round.

1:38:20.061 --> 1:38:21.794
[Beeping]

1:38:24.165 --> 1:38:25.398
Please don't.

1:38:25.533 --> 1:38:26.599
[Static]

1:38:26.735 --> 1:38:29.235
♪♪

1:38:29.371 --> 1:38:31.104
[Beep]

1:38:31.206 --> 1:38:32.805
♪♪

1:38:32.941 --> 1:38:35.008
Signal's cut.
Signal's cut.

1:38:35.143 --> 1:38:39.412
What do you see,
Gadi?

1:38:39.514 --> 1:38:41.781
If you've had no time
to yourself,

1:38:41.917 --> 1:38:43.850
then how are these
here now?

1:38:43.952 --> 1:38:46.819
They -- They --
They must've switched it.

1:38:46.922 --> 1:38:48.755
-They?
-Yeah, the police.

1:38:48.857 --> 1:38:51.224
They -- They checked my bag
when I gave over the case.

1:38:51.359 --> 1:38:53.593
You didn't say this.

1:38:53.695 --> 1:38:55.028
Gadi?

1:38:55.163 --> 1:38:59.198
♪♪

1:38:59.301 --> 1:39:00.633
[Thumps radio]

1:39:00.769 --> 1:39:04.304
♪♪

1:39:04.406 --> 1:39:06.406
Tell Picton's men
to surround the house.

1:39:06.541 --> 1:39:09.409
No one goes in
without my signal.

1:39:09.544 --> 1:39:12.345
♪♪

1:39:12.480 --> 1:39:14.714
Go.

1:39:14.849 --> 1:39:16.349
♪♪

1:39:16.484 --> 1:39:17.517
Gadi?

1:39:17.652 --> 1:39:20.720
♪♪

1:39:23.190 --> 1:39:29.395
[Charlie panting]

1:39:29.531 --> 1:39:31.230
Khalil:
Tell me the truth.

1:39:31.366 --> 1:39:35.401
[Breathing heavily]

1:39:35.537 --> 1:39:39.105
It's over.

1:39:39.174 --> 1:39:41.274
That's --
That's the truth.

1:39:41.376 --> 1:39:43.710
♪♪

1:39:43.845 --> 1:39:45.778
That was the signal.

1:39:45.914 --> 1:39:48.114
I was -- I was meant to wait
until you were asleep.

1:39:48.249 --> 1:39:49.615
We built the bomb.
I saw the news.

1:39:49.718 --> 1:39:52.218
No,
you saw the fiction.

1:39:52.320 --> 1:39:59.659
♪♪

1:39:59.794 --> 1:40:01.694
Who are you
working for?

1:40:01.796 --> 1:40:04.397
The Germans?
The British?

1:40:04.466 --> 1:40:06.466
No.

1:40:06.601 --> 1:40:10.303
♪♪

1:40:10.372 --> 1:40:13.573
The Zionists?

1:40:13.708 --> 1:40:15.308
Are you Jewish?

1:40:15.410 --> 1:40:17.577
No.

1:40:17.712 --> 1:40:20.313
♪♪

1:40:20.448 --> 1:40:23.116
Then what are you?

1:40:23.251 --> 1:40:26.652
♪♪

1:40:26.755 --> 1:40:29.055
Um...

1:40:29.190 --> 1:40:30.590
♪♪

1:40:30.692 --> 1:40:32.658
I'm an actress.

1:40:32.794 --> 1:40:35.395
So you don't believe
in anything?

1:40:35.497 --> 1:40:38.865
♪♪

1:40:39.000 --> 1:40:42.635
[Gasps]

1:40:42.771 --> 1:40:44.070
My brother.

1:40:44.205 --> 1:40:46.305
No, I-I never --
I never met him. [Sniffles]

1:40:46.408 --> 1:40:48.107
I never met him.
I only saw -- I saw him once.

1:40:48.209 --> 1:40:49.308
You killed him?

1:40:49.411 --> 1:40:51.544
Before they...

1:40:51.679 --> 1:40:54.313
♪♪

1:40:54.449 --> 1:40:56.516
I'm so sorry.

1:41:13.001 --> 1:41:15.535
I hope it was worth it.

1:41:26.748 --> 1:41:28.681
[Sighs]

1:41:30.785 --> 1:41:32.985
[Gunshot]
[Gasps]

1:41:33.121 --> 1:41:35.755
[Gunshots]

1:41:35.890 --> 1:41:38.091
[High-pitched ringing]

1:41:50.805 --> 1:41:52.371
Are you okay?

1:41:58.379 --> 1:42:03.116
[Breathing heavily]

1:42:22.704 --> 1:42:25.605
[Crying]

1:42:44.292 --> 1:42:45.858
Kurtz: Gadi.

1:42:45.960 --> 1:42:48.327
Picton: Dear, oh, dear.

1:42:48.463 --> 1:42:49.896
Don't worry, old boy.

1:42:50.031 --> 1:42:51.664
We'll ship him back to Tel Aviv
for you.

1:42:51.799 --> 1:42:53.466
No questions asked.

1:43:03.845 --> 1:43:05.945
[Sighs]

1:43:09.250 --> 1:43:11.684
Here.

1:43:24.299 --> 1:43:26.933
[Crying]

1:43:27.068 --> 1:43:29.268
[Gurney rattles]

1:43:32.507 --> 1:43:37.143
Can I -- Can I have a ci--
um, a cigarette?

1:43:38.146 --> 1:43:41.147
Can you remember
what he said to you, love?

1:43:41.249 --> 1:43:42.715
Hm?

1:43:42.817 --> 1:43:43.950
Yes.

1:43:44.052 --> 1:43:45.384
That's good.

1:43:45.486 --> 1:43:47.587
We'll talk about that
in a bit.

1:43:47.722 --> 1:43:50.690
Can you remember
further back?

1:43:50.792 --> 1:43:52.525
Can you remember
Lebanon?

1:43:52.660 --> 1:43:54.660
Yes.

1:43:54.762 --> 1:43:56.662
What did you see
out there?

1:43:56.731 --> 1:43:59.599
[Speaking inaudibly]

1:43:59.701 --> 1:44:07.106
♪♪

1:44:07.242 --> 1:44:14.113
♪♪

1:44:14.215 --> 1:44:20.686
♪♪

1:44:20.788 --> 1:44:23.155
Coordinates confirmed.

1:44:23.291 --> 1:44:28.794
33/44/38.4 north,

1:44:28.930 --> 1:44:34.267
33/25/17.0 east.

1:44:34.369 --> 1:44:38.337
[Jet engines roaring]

1:44:38.473 --> 1:44:41.474
[Explosion]

1:44:43.177 --> 1:44:46.178
[Tracking device beeping]

1:44:46.281 --> 1:44:49.749
[Rock music playing]

1:44:49.851 --> 1:44:54.186
♪♪

1:44:54.322 --> 1:44:55.388
[Gunshot]
[Gasps]

1:44:55.523 --> 1:44:57.490
♪♪

1:44:57.592 --> 1:45:00.593
[Gunshots]

1:45:00.728 --> 1:45:02.228
[Music stops]

1:45:02.363 --> 1:45:05.197
[Gasping]

1:45:05.333 --> 1:45:10.736
♪♪

1:45:10.872 --> 1:45:13.539
[Men conversing in German]

1:45:13.675 --> 1:45:14.907
Man:
<i> Danke, Herr Mesterbein.</i>

1:45:15.043 --> 1:45:16.909
Goodbye.<i> Tchuss.</i>
<i> -Tchuss.</i>

1:45:17.011 --> 1:45:20.279
♪♪

1:45:20.415 --> 1:45:23.249
[Humming]

1:45:23.384 --> 1:45:30.523
♪♪

1:45:30.625 --> 1:45:32.892
[Silenced gunshots]

1:45:32.994 --> 1:45:39.899
♪♪

1:45:39.967 --> 1:45:41.467
[Silenced gunshot]

1:45:41.569 --> 1:45:44.136
♪♪

1:45:44.272 --> 1:45:45.638
Woman:<i> Positive I.D. on Rossino.</i>

1:45:45.707 --> 1:45:54.980
♪♪

1:45:55.083 --> 1:46:03.923
♪♪

1:46:04.025 --> 1:46:06.359
[Dialing]

1:46:06.427 --> 1:46:08.327
[Telephone rings in distance]

1:46:08.429 --> 1:46:11.764
♪♪

1:46:11.899 --> 1:46:13.132
<i> Pronto?</i>

1:46:13.267 --> 1:46:15.501
This is for Gabriel.

1:46:15.603 --> 1:46:16.969
[Detonator clicks]

1:46:17.105 --> 1:46:19.305
[Explosion]

1:46:19.440 --> 1:46:22.274
[Screams, indistinct shouting]

1:46:22.377 --> 1:46:26.312
♪♪

1:46:26.447 --> 1:46:29.882
[Explosion]

1:46:48.702 --> 1:46:51.237
[Sighs]

1:46:58.146 --> 1:46:59.645
It's light.

1:46:59.781 --> 1:47:01.847
Thank you.

1:47:11.325 --> 1:47:20.566
♪♪

1:47:20.701 --> 1:47:30.009
♪♪

1:47:30.111 --> 1:47:39.185
♪♪

1:47:39.287 --> 1:47:48.327
♪♪

1:47:48.463 --> 1:47:57.503
♪♪

1:47:57.638 --> 1:48:06.645
♪♪

1:48:06.781 --> 1:48:15.354
♪♪

1:48:15.456 --> 1:48:19.191
[Brakes squeak,
engine shuts off]

1:48:19.327 --> 1:48:27.466
♪♪

1:48:27.568 --> 1:48:34.807
♪♪

1:48:34.909 --> 1:48:36.842
Here.

1:48:36.911 --> 1:48:39.411
[Bracelet clatters]

1:48:46.821 --> 1:48:50.656
[Sighs]

1:48:54.095 --> 1:48:56.028
Amsterdam.

1:48:56.163 --> 1:48:57.596
Last week.

1:48:57.732 --> 1:49:00.766
15 dead.

1:49:04.605 --> 1:49:07.973
You got us closer than anyone,
Charlie.

1:49:13.014 --> 1:49:15.981
Why did you
have him killed?

1:49:19.620 --> 1:49:23.188
That was not
my order.

1:49:23.324 --> 1:49:26.325
Khalil would have
gone on to become

1:49:26.427 --> 1:49:29.495
so much more
than a terrorist.

1:49:31.232 --> 1:49:32.965
[Scoffs]

1:49:35.336 --> 1:49:38.103
And Gadi stopped it.

1:49:40.708 --> 1:49:44.276
You cannot stop
the devil.

1:49:44.378 --> 1:49:48.213
Only the man
performing him.

1:49:52.320 --> 1:49:54.653
How is he?

1:49:57.692 --> 1:50:00.259
He will not
speak to me anymore.

1:50:00.394 --> 1:50:02.194
Ah.

1:50:09.837 --> 1:50:12.705
[Paper rustles]

1:50:18.245 --> 1:50:20.245
[Bracelet jingles]

1:50:46.607 --> 1:50:49.241
[Bells chiming]

1:50:51.946 --> 1:50:54.380
[Speaks German]

1:50:57.284 --> 1:50:59.318
[Car door closes]

1:51:01.589 --> 1:51:03.589
[Ball thudding]

1:51:11.966 --> 1:51:13.632
<i> Danke.</i>

1:51:13.768 --> 1:51:16.001
[Baby crying in distance]

1:51:16.137 --> 1:51:19.138
[Siren wails in distance]

1:51:31.352 --> 1:51:33.352
[Pruning shears clicking]

1:51:38.693 --> 1:51:40.826
[Teacup clinks]

1:51:42.997 --> 1:51:44.029
[Door squeaks]

1:51:44.165 --> 1:51:46.198
[Gasps]

1:51:50.638 --> 1:51:52.738
[Door closes]

1:52:01.315 --> 1:52:05.551
[Breathes deeply]

1:52:05.686 --> 1:52:08.921
Who are you?

1:52:09.023 --> 1:52:14.293
♪♪

1:52:14.428 --> 1:52:17.262
Who am I?

1:52:17.398 --> 1:52:19.364
♪♪

1:52:19.467 --> 1:52:23.068
One question at a time.

1:52:23.204 --> 1:52:25.003
[Chuckles]

1:52:25.139 --> 1:52:34.513
♪♪

